title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Combine beef, water and cabbage; cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Add beans, tomatoes, chili seasoning, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: philly-ham dip
directions: Soften and cream together the cream cheese and mayonnaise. Gradually add all other ingredients and mix until well blended and creamy.
Delicious with any type chips or crackers.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Put into 4 individual or 1 large casserole.
Sprinkle the cheese over and top with the chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: christmas ornaments
directions: Mix together, then knead.
Stick parts together with water. Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours until dry and hard.

title: ham 'n egg rice bake
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Cook rice by directions on package.
In bowl, beat eggs.
Add ham, onions and pepper.
Stir in rice mixture.
Spoon into greased plate.
Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, sugar and egg.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk.

title: coca cola pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper to taste and brown in skillet.
Place chops in 9x13 baking dish.
Mix ketchup, cola and 1 tablespoon of brown sugar; pour over chops.
Sprinkle with additional brown sugar.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Cook rice. If fresh onion is used, saute it into margarine.
Fold broccoli into rice.
Add salt and pepper.
Dilute soup with milk and fold into rice mixture.
Add onion and butter.
Mix thoroughly.

title: cherry charm
directions: Follow directions to prepare Dream Whip.
Mix cheese and sugar together and add to Dream Whip.
Spoon Dream Whip mix in crusts. Add layer of cherries.
Add layer of Dream Whip on top.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Chill in refrigerator overnight. Makes 2 pies.

title: our best baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for about 3 to 4 hours.

title: congealed salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in pineapple juice.
Add jello and stir well.
Let cool.
Add Dream Whip topping, cottage cheese and crushed pineapple and nuts.
Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs; add oil and mix well.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Add rice last.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch loaf pan for 50 minutes.

title: becky's turkey tacos
directions: Brown meat, add taco seasonings and 1 tablespoon water. Simmer to blend flavors.
Warm tortillas; spoon in meat and choice of toppings.
Enjoy this low fat main dish with refried beans and rice.

title: chewy cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add other ingredients and mix.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes or until center is formed.

title: bacon-cheese mashed potatoes
directions: Place the potatoes and 1 teaspoon salt in a heavy 4-quart saucepan and cover with water by 1-inch. Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to a simmer and cook until the potatoes are fork-tender, about 20 minutes. Drain in a colander and return to the cooking pot. Add the cream, butter, remaining 3/4 teaspoon salt and black pepper. Place the pan over medium-low heat and mash with a potato masher to mix the ingredients and get a light texture, about 4 to 5 minutes. Add the bacon, grated cheese, sour cream and chopped chives and stir until thoroughly combined. Season to taste. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: best ever chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in a microwave mixing bowl.
Stir in milk, chocolate syrup and eggs.
Stir well.
Put in microwave for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes with wire whisk until thick. Take out of microwave and add butter and vanilla; stir until melted.
Pour into crust.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs; add allspice and cocoa.
Alternate milk and flour.
Add baking powder and raisins.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Mix together and sprinkle with nutmeg.
You can use this with grapes (white seedless), honeydew melon balls, apple slices, peach slices, watermelon balls, strawberries, bananas, pineapple or any other fruit may be used.
Arrange in layers and pour dressing over.

title: kolaches
directions: Make a sponge of yeast, milk and about 3 cups of flour. Cover and
let
rise for 1 hour.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and
egg yolks.
Add
flour
gradually and work with a wooden paddle or your mixer until the dough is smooth and not sticky. You may not have to use all the flour measured out.

title: grandmaw's gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and molasses.
Beat egg with buttermilk; add to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients, 1/3 at a time; mix well after each addition.
Add more flour (if needed) to make stiff dough.
Fill bowl about 1/2 full of flour.
Place dough in center and knead.
Pinch off dough size of a peach and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten a little.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: 7-up beef
directions: Place beef in casserole dish.
Pour onion soup mix on top. Add soup.
Pour 7-Up over beef, onion and soup mixture.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours (or 250° for 3 hours).
Do not open while cooking. Serve over rice.

title: fr. john's pralines
directions: Mix sugar, soda, milk and Karo syrup.
Stir over medium heat until mixture forms a ball.
Add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Put
pickle lime in enough water to cover tomatoes; let stand for 24 hours.
Rinse well (about 5 or 6 times to be sure all lime is	off).
Soak in fresh ice water 4 hours.
(Change water every hour.)

title: minced onion recipe lemon herb chicken
directions: Cut-up 1 frying chicken.
Arrange in bottom of a shallow pan. Melt butter and blend with other ingredients.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Spoon butter mixture over chicken occasionally.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pesto shortbread
directions: Beat butter and Parmesan cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Add garlic and next 3 ingredients, beating just till blended.
Gradually stir in flour with a spoon (mixture will become crumbly); stir until mixture is blended and smooth, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Or instead of stirring the dough with a spoon after adding flour, you can gently press mixture with hands and work until blended and smooth.

title: betty's luscious lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg (slightly beaten) and melted butter together.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, 3 slightly beaten eggs, powdered sugar and lemon extract.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lazy day casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole dish and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked italian chicken
directions: Pour corn flakes into gallon Ziploc bag that has chicken and Italian dressing.
Roll breast in corn flakes until well coated. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients except cake mix, nuts and butter and pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour 1 box yellow cake mix over the mixture evenly.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts over the cake mix evenly.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks butter and pour over the cake/nut topping.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and celery in salted water until tender; drain.
Add half and half to soup.
Pour over squash and toss lightly.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix 1/2 cup flour with dates, nuts, candy and coconut.
Cream sugar and butter together well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Cream well.
Alternate flour mixture and buttermilk mixture.
Add nuts and fruits.
Bake in a greased and floured angel food pan or 3 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: nut loaf
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and stir in.
Add nuts, cherries and raisins. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Pour into a large baking dish.	Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cracker treats
directions: Cook dates, Eagle Brand milk and chopped pecans until thick. Spread on Town House crackers.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Mix the margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla; spread on the baked crackers.
Store in tight container and keep in the refrigerator.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat butter, salt, light brown sugar and corn syrup to boiling. Boil for five minutes on medium heat.
Do not stir.
Remove from stove.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
It will foam up.
Pour over popped corn in a large baking pan.
Heat oven to 250°.
Bake for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet; drain well.
Put all ingredients in large pot and cook slow for 30 minutes or until done.
Add more water if needed.

title: christmas salad
directions: Grind together the cranberries and oranges.
Mix all together and let set in fridge until firm.

title: simple cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth. Add cheese until it is melted.

title: savory brisket of beef
directions: Trim fat from brisket.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients and pour over brisket in roasting pan.
Roast covered between 250° to 275° for 4 hours.
Let stand 20 to 30 minutes before slicing.
Serve with pan juices.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cinnamon and cloves.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Beat sugar with eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add milk; cook over medium heat.
Stirring constantly, cook until mixture coats spoon.
Remove from heat and add chopped candy bars, vanilla and condensed milk.
Pour into gallon freezer; add enough milk to fill container.
Leave 2 inches.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: snow mountain cake
directions: Beat eggs and 1 cup sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. Stir in vanilla, dates and nuts.
Spread in two 8-inch oiled pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: leftover turkey(over rice or noodles)
directions: Melt margarine over low heat; blend in flour and seasonings. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and cream or milk.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in turkey or chicken and simmer.

title: low-fat cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers. Mix with melted margarine. Press into pie plate. Blend cottage cheese in blender until smooth. Mix diet Jell-O with water; add to cottage cheese. Add Cool
Whip. Put in pie plate and sprinkle graham crackers on top. Refrigerate.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Melt 4 tablespoons margarine in an 8-inch square pan.
Spread evenly and arrange apples over it.
Mix 1/4 teaspoon salt with 1/4 cup sugar and sprinkle over apples.
Set aside.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and corn syrup until firm ball stage.
Add peanuts and cook until golden brown.
Remove from heat and add soda, vanilla and butter.
Pour into an 8-inch pie pan to cool. Makes 4 or 5 (1/4-inch) patties.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown sausage in frying
pan.
Cut up cheese in cubes and place in large, microwave-safe bowl.
Add Ro-Tel to the cheese and microwave until cheese is completely melted; stir often.
After cheese is melted, add sausage and mix thoroughly.
Dip in chips and enjoy.

title: swiss cheese mustard bread
directions: Slice French bread about 3/4 way down every 1-inch, leaving loaf together at the bottom.
Place slices of cheese into slots.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Combine ingredients in a glass bowl.
Beat well.
Cover and let stand 2 days in warm place.
It must have air.
Do not refrigerate.
After 1 week you may give a cup to a friend.
To replenish as used add 1 cup water, 1 cup flour and 1 cup sugar.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Blend together all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a 2-quart non-metallic bowl. Cover with wax paper and towel and set at room temperature for 48 hours.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
After 48 hours, cover with a tight fitting cover and refrigerate.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake per directions. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan and pour half the batter in. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
In a saucepan, melt caramels over low heat. Add milk and butter. Remove cake from oven and pour mixture over cake.
Add chocolate chips and nuts. Pour remaining cake batter over the top and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: grape punch
directions: Blend sugar and water; mix well.
Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes; let cool.
Add grape juice or juice and ginger ale. Chill.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender at one time and blend until mixed together.
Pour into a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. When done, crust will be on the bottom, custard in the middle and coconut on top, right where they belong!!

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cucumber slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and toss well with mayonnaise and salad dressing.
Can add more or less to taste.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Bring mushrooms with broth to a boil in saucepan.
Add peas. Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Uncover and add ham.
Heat and stir until broth is absorbed and peas are tender-crisp.
Toss cooked macaroni, green pepper and tomatoes with salad dressing.
Stir in mushroom-pea-ham mixture.
Chill.
Turn into salad bowl lined with spinach leaves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican enchiladas
directions: Cook and drain beef.
Add soup, seasoning and beans.
Start with beef mixture and layer with flour tortillas in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: my chocolate dream
directions: You will also need one 10-inch or 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add flour, salt and soda. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain well, mash until smooth with potato masher.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, onion salt, salt, pepper and butter.
Beat or mash until smooth and fluffy.
Put in greased casserole, dot with butter.
Chill for 3 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix first four items and roll into ball.
Roll ball onto nuts. Serve.

title: champion salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar; mix well.
Add diced bananas, fresh or frozen strawberries, crushed pineapple and chopped pecans.
Fold in container of Cool Whip.
Freeze until 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix with 2 beaten eggs and pour over a 9-inch pie shell filled with 3 cups of cut-up rhubarb.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; then at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut fancy pieces of crust for top of pie before baking.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Arrange stalks in greased 12 x 7-1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken atop.
Combine next 3 ingredients. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and oleo.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Serves 6-8.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Combine meat, onion and garlic in a large skillet. Cook over medium heat until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Add next 7 ingredients and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan; press firmly to sides and bottom of pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Do not mix (important). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
In a large skillet, cook onions in margarine until tender, but not browned.
Stir in salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits; place in ungreased 5 x 10 inch jelly roll pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2 inch sides to form crust.
Spoon onions over crust; sprinkle with bacon.
In medium bowl, combine cream, sour cream and eggs until well blended; stir in cheese.
Spoon evenly over onions and bacon. Sprinkle with additional pepper.
Bake at 375 degrees for 24 - 30 minutes or until crust is deep golden brown.
Store in refrigerator.
12 servings.

title: glazed onion rings
directions: Peel onions and cut into even, thin slices.
Heat butter in large skillet.
Add onions and toss for a few minutes until coated with butter.
Do not brown.
Add vinegar, brown sugar and curry powder.
Stir to blend well.
Add parsley.

title: florida's key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Blend in condensed milk slowly.
Add lime juice and mix well.

title: chocolate glazed triple layer cheesecake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter in a medium bowl, blending well.
Press into bottom and 2-inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
Mix in casserole with rest of ingredients.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: sweet and sour kraut salad
directions: Combine vinegar and sugar in small saucepan. Boil; set aside to cool.
Drain kraut thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and pour vinegar and sugar mixture over all.
Cover and place in refrigerator until serving time.
Salad may be stored in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in pan.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.
These are the best!

title: mounds bar
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit preserves
directions: Bring to boil (rolling).
Drop fruit in and cook for 2 hours. Use this with any kind of fruit, peaches, apples, figs, etc.

title: wedding cookies with cream cheese
directions: Cream the cheese with oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg yolk.
Cream well, adding flour a little at a time.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost cookies when cooled.

title: true ginger bread(very good)
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
grease an 8 inch square pan.
In bowl with electric mixer on medium speed, cream together butter and sugar.
Add molasses, corn syrup, egg, and salt and beat until smooth.

title: "the chicken"
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, leaving skin on.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large measuring cup.
Pour over chicken.
Place in refrigerator at least 1 hour (overnight is best).
When ready to bake, turn oven to 350°.
Leave chicken out at room temperature for 1/2 hour.
Pour 1 cup white wine over chicken and sauce.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: banana bread(double recipe for 2 loaves)
directions: Mix all together.
Grease loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
To serve, place 3 teaspoons mixture in a cup and add hot water.
Recipe may be doubled to use as gift.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Roll chicken in crescent rolls and place in a casserole dish.
Mix both soups and broth together; mix well.
Add Veg-All.
Pour over crescent rolls and bake at 350° until done.
Rolls will float to top and bake golden brown.

title: beef stew
directions: Season beef stew with salt and pepper; brown it in Crisco. Remove oil from pot, then put meat back in pot.
Add water and onion.
Cook until almost done, then add tomatoes and potatoes. Please season to your taste.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 10 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: turkey and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter in a large skillet until vegetables are tender; set aside.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Cut spears in half; arrange in a greased, shallow 2-quart casserole.
Combine sauteed vegetables and remaining ingredients; spoon over broccoli.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until heated.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Whip cream; fold in salad dressing and add remaining ingredients.
Fold gently until mixed; chill.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet crispix mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal, pecans and almonds in a roasting pan, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Add brown sugar, stirring until dissolved. Stir in corn syrup.
Bring to a boil, over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal mixture; toss to coat.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on 10 x 15-inch baking sheets.
Cool.
Break into large pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and oil.
Mix rest of ingredients, except eggs.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk until smooth and add Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13 inch pan with graham crackers and then put a layer of pudding mixture, then a layer of graham crackers, then pudding. End with layer of graham crackers.
Chill for 1 hour.
Spread icing on top of crackers.
Place in freezer 1 hour before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Butter lightly and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam; set aside.
Cook bacon until brown and crispy; drain well.
Crumble over bread; then sprinkle cheese over bacon.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt.
Mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover casserole and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator for 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: honey butter
directions: Mix well with mixer and pack in cup size containers. Store in the refrigerator. Keeps for about 2 weeks. This makes about 4 cups.

title: soft frosting
directions: Mix together milk, flour and water. Bring to boil, stirring constantly, to avoid lumps.
Set aside when thick and let cool. Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.

title: mother's chicken hawaiian
directions: Melt butter with soy sauce and onion.
Bring to a boil and pour over the chicken.
Bake in a 400° oven on the top rack for an hour or until tender.
Add the peaches or pineapple halves the last 10 minutes.

title: new potato salad
directions: Boil new potatoes for 15 to 20 minutes until tender. Cool, then slice into 1/4-inch slices. Combine all ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: orange french toast
directions: Beat eggs and add all remaining ingredients except bread.
Mix well.
Coat the bread slices with the batter.
Place in a single layer in a dish.
Pour the remaining batter over the bread layer. Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add the French toast a few pieces at a time and saute until nicely browned. Serve immediately.

title: emerald salad
directions: Sprinkle Cool Whip with jello in a mixing bowl.
Pour in fruit, cottage cheese and bananas.
Fold in with fork.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour or more.
May leave out bananas.
Also you may use pink jello, like cherry, raspberry or strawberry.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add pineapple and pie filling. Pour in 13 x 9 x 2 pan and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Do not over mix.
Pour mixture into pie shell, and chill for 2 hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix Nabisco All Bran and boiling water; let cool.
Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Add All Bran and water mixture.
Fold in Kellogg's Bran.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Slowly add moist ingredients, mixing well.
Add chocolate chips last.
Bake in large baking dish at 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Steam cauliflower.
Blend egg, mayo, pepper, cheese and onion. Strain cauliflower and mix in sauce.
Put in buttered casserole dish and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cracker snacks
directions: Put crackers in large bowl.
Add seasonings then pour oil over all.
Stir every 15 minutes for three times.
Let sit for 2 hours. Store in Ziplock bags.
So-o-o Good!

title: taco cheese pie
directions: Brown beef well; drain off fat.
Put beef and remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on high 1 hour, stirring until cheese is fully melted.
Serve immediately or turn on low for serving up to 6 hours later.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.
Recipe can be doubled.
Great for large parties.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in oil.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone.
Cut into pieces; put in a greased Pyrex bowl.
Mix other ingredients; pour over chicken. Crush crackers; mix with melted margarine until well coated. Spread over the top of casserole.
Bake at 325° until crumbs are crisp, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 12 x 18-inch pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
A disposable aluminum cookie sheet with a lip works well.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Put filling in bottom of dish.
Pour dry cake mix over filling.
Cover top with thinly sliced butter.
Combine nuts, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over top.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Allow to steep on low for about 2 or 3 hours.

title: rotel chicken
directions: they have a tale to tell.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture. Fold topping into mixture.
Sprinkle top with chopped peanuts and freeze.

title: patty's broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat home with love to tenth degree.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk. Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture. Divide dough in half; chill 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and melted oleo.
Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
(Use 9-inch unbaked pie shell.)

title: broccoli or squash casserole
directions: After broccoli or squash is cooked, also the rice, mix all other ingredients together; add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish and top with crushed Hi Ho crackers.
Bake at 350° until casserole browns on top, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Mix well. Dip bread and lightly brown in frying pan. Top with syrup, jelly or confectioners sugar.

title: jerky
directions: Place a layer of meat in pan that can be covered. Sprinkle with part of mixture of salts; another layer of meat strips and then seasonings. Do this until all meat and salt is gone. Cover pan and place in refrigerator overnight. Place meat touching but not overlapping on a cookie sheet. Put in oven at 175° to 200° for 4 to 5 hours. Store in tightly covered jar or bag.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Remove fat and skin from chicken.
Cut from bone and strip meat.
Add salt, pepper and m.s.g.
Place oil in wok and preheat to 325°.
Add chicken to hot oil and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Cook until chicken turns whites.
Add onions, mushrooms, pimento and stir-fry 1 minute.
Add broth, sherry, peas or beans.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Combine water and cornstarch.
Stir.
Add to center of wok and boil about 1 minute. Stir and cook 1 more minute, until sauce is thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: eggs creole
directions: Bring water to a boil, gradually stir in grits and return to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from heat and stir in sausage and next 3 ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; pressing firmly and smoothing surface.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Turn grits out onto wax paper and cut out rounds with a biscuit cutter (reserve remaining for other use).
Sprinkle rounds with flour; combine egg and milk.
Dip into egg mixture and dredge in breadcrumbs.
Pour oil to 1-inch depth; fry grits in hot oil over medium heat, 1 to 2 minutes until lightly browned; drain on paper towels.
Place 2 rounds on plate and top with poached egg and Creole Sauce.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls in skillet with small amount of oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn once while cooking.

title: nannie's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and peanut butter with the vanilla. Add egg; beat.
Combine flour and soda (sifted) with salt.
Add small amounts at a time to sugar mixture.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook salt pork in bottom of kettle.
Add onions, potatoes and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add corn.
Simmer 5 minutes longer. Stir in milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Heat.
Don't boil.
Remove salt pork.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Mix in flour and chips.
Spread into 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spanish cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in shallow casserole that has been greased with 1 teaspoon canola oil.
Add seasonings to tomatoes and bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over cauliflower.
Top with crumbs and dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar for 5 minutes; cool.
Add remaining ingredients; refrigerate.

title: taco bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 hour or more.
Serve with your favorite toppings: grated sharp cheese, jalapeno Jack cheese, tortilla chips, sour cream, or salsa and jalapeno peppers.
This recipe doubles easily and freezes well.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour fruit in bottom of pan; pour dry cake mix on top.
Cut 2 sticks of butter on top of cake mix.
Spread with nuts.
Cook in oven at 325° until done, about 1 hour.

title: mother's shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix with green beans and corn.
Stir in tomatoes; salt and pepper.
Spoon into 2 buttered pie pans.
Beat eggs and blend in mashed potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread potato mix over ground beef mixture. Spread and seal to edge of pan.
Sprinkle with cheese evenly. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses get to room temperature.
In a large bowl, mix the two cheeses together.
It is easiest to use your hands.
Mix it really, really good.
Add garlic powder, a little at a time.
The garlic taste will get stronger as it sets.
Mix it all really well.
Form into a ball.
Roll in parsley and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: t. j. miracle soup
directions: Chop all vegetables and cover with plenty of water, adding the soup mix.
Cook slowly about 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together in large bowl both soups and milk.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Pour into large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican style cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Grease a 9x13-inch aluminum pan. Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 425 degrees for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef medley soup
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add next 6 ingredients and 1 1/2 quarts water.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour longer.
Makes 3 quarts or 6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with 1 gallon water.
Sweeten with sugar to your taste.
Freeze.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar and let stand.
Put butter in a 2-quart casserole and place in oven to melt.
Combine remaining sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Spoon peaches on top of batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: noodle spinach ring
directions: Cook
noodles
until barely tender; drain.
Mix noodles and spinach.
Saute
onions in butter until tender.
Mix eggs and sour
cream and fold in all other ingredients.
Pour into greased 6-cup mold.
Place mold in pan of hot water in a 350° oven	and cook 45 minutes.
Unmold onto heated platter.
Good served with mushrooms or carrots in center of mold.
Serves 8.

title: braised beef tips over rice(serves 6)
directions: Melt shortening; brown meat on all sides.
Stir in consomme, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion salt.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cook on simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Blend cornstarch and water and stir in.
Cook until thickens.

title: baked yellow rice(nasi kuning, singapore)
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (190°C).
Place rice in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add butter, salt, curry powder and turmeric.
Add boiling water; stir until butter melts.
Cover tightly; bake 25 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Fluff with a fork before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gold star chili dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Cover with 1 can Gold Star chili.
Evenly sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of chili.
Microwave on High until chili is hot and cheese is melted or bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with jalapenos and/or diced tomatoes (optional).
Serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: fruit cake(uncooked)
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk slowly.
Mix all other ingredients. Pour hot milk mixture over ingredients.
Stir together and pack in buttered stem pan.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Remove excess fat from the meat and add chopped onion and seasoning. Mix thoroughly and place in the bottom of a fireproof dish.
Add stock and place potatoes on top.
Smooth and mark with a fork.
Bake at 200° C for 1/2 hour until thoroughly heated.
Top should be well browned.

title: barbecue
directions: Combine ingredients and cook for several hours.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: strawberries and cream
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and chill.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and sugar and margarine to a boil.
Add baking powder and flour all at once and stir quickly until it becomes like a paste and comes away from the pot.
Let it cool; when cooled add eggs, one at a time and beat after each addition.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake about 20 minutes or until golden color. After cooled, slice to prepare for filling.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Parboil chicken.
Put cut-up chicken (cut in chunks) in oblong dish.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.
Toss crumbs with butter and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, salt, soda and eggs.
Stir in fruit cocktail.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle nut meats on top of batter, then sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake at 350° until tests done.
Top with fruit cocktail dressing while hot.

title: oven stew
directions: Bake at 325° for 5 hours, uncovered.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: zesty squash
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, microwave butter and garlic on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Mix in oregano, basil, salt and pepper, adding remaining ingredients except tomato.
Toss to coat and cover.
Microwave on High until squash is tender, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 1/2 the cooking time.
Stir in tomato and cover. Let stand 2 minutes.

title: chicken pita for one
directions: Stuff pita with ingredients.

title: apricot pie
directions: Mix apricots, drained, in blender.
Soak gelatin in water; set aside.
Heat apricot juice.
Add gelatin, sugar, salt, lemon juice and apricots.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
(Hint: Have everything measured and ready before heating the apricot juice.)
Cool on counter for 10 minutes, then put in refrigerator until it begins to set.
Beat 1/2 of heavy cream (don't add any sugar).
Fold into apricot mixture and pour into graham cracker crust.
Put back in refrigerator; let set until hard.
When ready to serve, beat the rest of the heavy cream, adding sugar to taste.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well with beater and pour into deep casserole.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Mix well drained fruit well. Add cottage cheese and stir. Pour dry Jell-O over mixture and stir well. Add Cool Whip and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Let cool, then pour over uncooked, unpeeled shrimp. Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Broil 15 to 20 minutes, turning shrimp frequently.
Sauce covers 6 to 8 pounds of shrimp.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Put chips and milk in a large saucepan. Melt over medium low heat until chips combine when stirred. Remove from heat. Measure out 1/2 cup and set aside for final step. Stir crumbs, marshmallows, nuts, confectioners sugar and salt into saucepan with remaining mixture. Press into 9 x 9-inch greased pan or line it with wax paper. Add 2 teaspoons evaporated milk to reserved chocolate mixture. Spread evenly over brownies. Chill and cut into 36 squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and drain.
Prepare stuffing according to directions, using 1/2 cup less water.
Add soup and milk to stuffing and add squash.
Put into casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 325° to 350° until bubbly and cheese is melted, about 25 minutes.

title: hamburger, macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Fry hamburger until light brown.
Saut onions in fat.
Pour in tomatoes and simmer 30 minutes.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour in casserole and sprinkle a little of the cheese on top and bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated carrots around edge of crust.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk; cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Beat until stiff.
Pour in pan (buttered 9 x 13-inch); let it cool.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and pecans. Mix well.
Roll into small balls and bake on cookie sheet for 1 hour at 275°.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
While oven is heating, melt 1/4 cup (1/2 stick) butter in a pie plate in oven.
When butter melts, stir in pecans.
Bake, stirring frequently, until pecans are toasted, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Chop onion and pepper.
In a large skillet, saute onion and pepper until partially done.
Add hamburger and cook until done. Drain.
In a separate skillet, saute sliced zucchini in small amount of oil or butter until slightly cooked.
In a large saucepan, heat spaghetti sauce and add drained hamburger mixture. Layer zucchini and sauce mixture in casserole dish, starting and ending with zucchini.
Sprinkle generously with grated cheese. Bake at 350° to 375° until cheese melts.

title: delicious king's pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk with lemon juice.
Fold in pineapple, whipped topping and walnuts.
Mix well and pour into crust.
Refrigerate.
This freezes well.
Makes 2 pies.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice zucchini in half lengthwise; scoop out centers and chop.
Arrange shells in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook chopped zucchini and onion in margarine until tender.
In large bowl combine zucchini onion mixture with ground beef, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, oregano, pepper, catsup and egg.
Spoon into shells.
Pour tomato sauce over mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Serves 4.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg yolks, flour, lemon and milk.
Beat egg whites very stiff; add last, folding in.
Put in casserole.
Set in a pan of hot water.
Bake for 45 minutes in a slow (350°) oven.
Forms custard below and solid on top.

title: jennifer's paradise punch
directions: In a large container, combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate. Makes 2 gallons.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Drop macaroni into the rapidly boiling water.
Add 3 teaspoons salt and cook rapidly for 8 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Turn into colander to drain.
Run
hot water through to rinse well. Melt butter; blend in flour and add milk and water.
Stir over direct heat until sauce boils and thickens, then stir in egg, salt and grated cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Arrange macaroni and cheese sauce in layers in a buttered casserole dish. Bake in a moderate oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese sauce is toasted.
Yields 5 servings.

title: bark tidbits
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave and pour over dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Allow to harden.
Can use Honey Nut Cheerios, Crispix in place of Captain Crunch.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cut them into small pieces.
Steam celery in 1/4 cup of water and drain.

title: tiger's butter
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler over low heat. (Separately!)

title: six hour stew
directions: Place meat in a heavy pot with tight seal lid.
Add vegetables.
Mix and sprinkle on tapioca and salt.
Mix again. Tear 2 slices of white bread into pieces.
Place on top of stew mix.
Pour the tomatoes over all or add the V-8 juice if desired. Cook at 250° for 6 hours. Do not open or disturb.
Stir before serving.
Serve with cornbread.

title: blender ice cream
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a blender and blend for 30 seconds. Add frozen peaches and blend for 1 minute.
Serve or freeze.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate spoon cake
directions: *Freeze and roll with rolling pin or "whack" with back of ice cream scoop.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Save broth.
If you don't have enough to make 2 quarts, then add a can of chicken broth.
Cook large size package of spaghetti in broth.
Add salt to suit taste.
Put into a skillet
butter and fry onions with a pinch of minced parsley.
Then add Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce, dash of red pepper and mushrooms, juice and all.
If you don't feel as if there is enough sauce, add a can of tomato soup. About half hour before serving, add chicken and 1/2 pound sharp cheese.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind Oreo cookies until black like dirt.
Mix remaining ingredients until creamy.
Layer Oreo cookies and filling into new flowerpot.
Put remaining Oreos on top of pot to make look like dirt.
Place artificial flower in center of pot.
Makes a nice centerpiece for table.
Chill overnight.

title: bordelaise sauce
directions: In small saucepan, cook mushrooms in butter till tender, about 4 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and beef broth.
Blend into mushrooms.
Cook and stir till mixture boils.
Add remaining ingredients and dash pepper.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cook in square pan.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients as for any batter.
Fold in beaten whites of eggs last.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes.
Boil until tender. Drain well.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Chop eggs and add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Chill for two (2) hours before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apple slices in bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Blend thoroughly oatmeal, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter. Sprinkle mixture over apples. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix the German chocolate cake mix as directed on package.
Mix cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Marble mixture in cake mix. Sprinkle chocolate chips over cake mix.
Bake approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Best when served warm.
No need to frost.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and put in a baking dish. In a pan, melt 1/2 of the butter; add Cheez Whiz and bring to a boil. Pour mixture over Veg-All. Crush crackers and mix with other half of melted butter. Put on top of Veg-All mixture; bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix according to package.
Grease 9x13 in pan.
Add nuts and coconut to pan and pour cake over top.
Cream together cream cheese, oleo and sugar.
Drop by teaspoonful over cake then bake at 350° for 45 mins.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cover cube steaks with flour and brown in margarine in large electric frypan.
When meat is browned, add soup and tomatoes. Add water as needed if gravy gets too thick.
Cook at lowest heat in electric frypan for 3 to 4 hours so your meat will be tender.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth. Spread on pie crust.
Add strawberries on top of cheese.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Prepare pie filling with 1 cup milk.
Fold in 1 cup of whipped topping.
Spoon over berries and chill until set.
Garnish with additional berries and remaining whipped topping.

title: quick beefy mac and cheese
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger meat, onion, mushrooms and salt and pepper to taste.
Drain meat mixture.
Mix in large serving bowl, prepared macaroni and cheese and hamburger meat.
Serve with salad or vegetable.

title: d d's low-fat fish
directions: Have Dr.
Claude Smith go fishing and bring you some fish all cleaned and filleted and in Baggies.
Cut up onions, mushrooms, celery and lemon and saute with olive oil.
Add seasonings to the mixture and then the wine.
Gently add fish and cook at medium-low temperature, about 15 minutes or until done.
(Works well with trout, catfish and even cheap fish, better if fish is fresh.)

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cut up peeled pumpkin and take out seeds.
Cook until soft in water.

title: mocha sundaes
directions: For fudge sauce, combine chocolate, sugar, evaporated milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted.
Serve warm or cold over scoops of coffee ice cream atop slices of chocolate pound cake.

title: alice's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar and flour.
Add Karo, vanilla and nuts, then add melted butter.
Mix well and pour into uncooked pastry shell.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: nanny's brownies
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Pour in melted butter, vanilla, eggs and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: party wieners
directions: Combine mustard with jelly. Add wieners and sugar; bring to a boil. Add wieners that are cut into small pieces. Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate supreme
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine; stir in flour, 1/2 cup pecans, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix well.
Spray bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam spray.
Mash flour mixture into bottom of pan and bake at 325° until light brown, about 30 minutes.
Allow to cool completely.

title: classic cooked egg nog
directions: In a large saucepan, beat together eggs, sugar and salt.
Stir in 2 cups milk.

Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick enough to coat a metal spoon or reaches 160°. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining 2 cups milk and vanilla. Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Just before serving, pour into a bowl or pitcher.
Garnish or add Stir-ins, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon frappe
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in container of blender; process until smooth.
Spoon into pitcher; stir in ginger ale.
Serve immediately.

title: homemade sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles and rinse.
Cut the ends off and slice.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir and let stand overnight, then keep refrigerated.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Sauce:
Heat butter, mushrooms and lemon juice.
Add flour, salt, paprika and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add chicken broth and half and half.
Stir and bring to boil until mixture thickens.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan:

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger in a large pan.
Drain.
Saute chopped onion and pepper with hamburger 2 to 3 minutes.
Add other ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes to let spices blend.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Cream this together and spread on bread cut into any shape you wish.
Top this with a slice of cucumber.
(I always peel mine.)

title: texas walnut crab cakes(prep time: 15 minutes; cook time: 10 minutes)
directions: Combine mashed potato flakes, pico de gallo, chopped walnuts, drained crabmeat, beaten eggs and green onion dip.
Shape crab mixture into 8 patties (1/4 cup each).
Heat a large skillet over medium high heat for 3 minutes.
Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray and cook crab cakes on each side for 3 to 4 minutes. Serve hot with lemon wedges and lemon butter sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Place broccoli in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake until tender. Drain off liquid.
Add the onion, soup, milk, water and cubed cheese to the broccoli.
Place in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese with confectioners sugar until creamy. Add the milk and peanut butter; mix well.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Put into a graham cracker crust.
Keep in freezer until serving time.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Measure shortening or margarine while cold.
Put in mixing bowl to soften at room temperature.
While softening, grease cookie sheet lightly.
Sift flour and measure.
To the flour add soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and raisins.
If raisins are sticking together, separate them and dust with flour before adding to flour mixture.
Stir well with batter beater.
Set oven at 350°.
By now shortening is ready.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Measure milk and add after eggs.
Beat well.
Measure oats and add with flour mixture to the creamed shortening mixture, a small amount at a time.
Mix well.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa in bowl.
Stir in milk and margarine.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in square pan, 9 x 9-inch.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over entire batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
During baking, cake mixture rises to top and chocolate sauce settles to bottom.
Cut into squares; invert each square onto dessert plate.
Spoon sauce over.
Serve warm.

title: molasses cake
directions: A pound of patience, you must find

title: beef or deer jerky
directions: Slice venison or beef in 1/8-inch strips.
This is easier if it is slightly frozen.
Combine ingredients and meat; marinate overnight.
Put on racks for excess marinade to drain off.
Put in dehydrator and cook until meat is completely dry, about 5 to 6 hours.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat egg, milk and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour batter in funnel and swirl into hot oil.
Remove from oil when light brown and sprinkle powdered sugar on it.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken, debone and cut into small pieces.
Place in large (9 inch x 13 inch) baking dish.
Mix broth and chicken soup really well and pour over chicken.

title: double decker fudge
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, Marshmallow Creme, evaporated milk, butter or margarine and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils.
Boil gently, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes.
Divide mixture in half.
To one half (about 3 cups), add chocolate pieces; stir until melted and blended.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
To remaining half of marshmallow mixture, add the butterscotch pieces; beat until smooth.
(If necessary, beat with rotary beater until pieces are melted and mixture is smooth.)
Pour over chocolate layer; cool.
Cut in pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done (may add salt to water, if desired).
Remove from water; let cool.
Pick meat off bones and place in bottom of a casserole dish.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth. Serve with fruit.

title: pie crust for strawberry pie
directions: Mix with fork; press into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes, or until brown.
Makes 1 crust.
Fill with your favorite strawberry filling.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat together the sugar, butter and Crisco until creamy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add cocoa and vanilla.
Add flour and buttermilk (alternating the dry ingredients with the liquid and beginning and ending with flour).
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: grilled green beans
directions: Place drained beans on a large double thick square of aluminum foil which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Top with tomatoes.
Cream together onion, butter, brown sugar, salt, mustard, horseradish and pepper.
Dot mixture over tomatoes.
Wrap securely in foil, sealing edges.
Place on grill and heat with cover down for 30 to 40 minutes on low flame setting.

title: chicken ceylon style
directions: Mix buttermilk and garlic powder in bowl.
Add chicken and let marinate 2 hours or more.
Baste and turn often, at room temperature.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thinly. Grease baking dish and place a row of potatoes in it. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour and dot with butter.
Add a row of thinly sliced onion and sprinkle again. Pour scalded milk over the last layer and dot with butter.
Bake at 370° for 1 hour.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage in skillet.
Remove sausage from skillet and crumble.
Cook green pepper and onion in a little of sausage grease.
Drain onion and pepper on paper towel.
Place onion and green pepper in bottom of pie pan.
Place sausage in shells.
Mix flour and cheese together.
Place over sausage.
Mix eggs and milk (beat well).
Pour into shells.
Sprinkle top with red pepper. Bake at 350° until done.
Can be frozen.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute celery, onion and butter. Add chicken stock and seasonings. Simmer 15 minutes. Slowly add mushroom soup. Add cheese. Boil spaghetti; rinse. Add this to other mixture. Let stand on warm eye. Add chicken. Put in shallow casserole (10-inch). Sprinkle with pecans and olives. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: butter crunch candy
directions: Melt butter in pot.
Add sugar and simmer for about 15 minutes until caramel color.
Pour over crackers that have been laid out on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over.
Return to oven and turn oven off.
Wait 5 minutes and remove pan.
Spread melted chips evenly.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Cool, then break up or cut into squares.

title: clam chowder
directions: Dry out the pork or bacon and fry the onion in the fat.
Add the clam liquor, water and potatoes.
Cook until tender; season. Add the clams and milk.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Then thicken with the butter and flour, creamed together.
Pour the chowder over the crackers and sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: peanut butter chip brownies
directions: Mix until of spreading consistency.

title: tuna melt
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients with Best Foods light mayonnaise; season with salt and paprika to taste.
Spread filling on top of English muffin halves and top each half with a piece of cheese.
Place in toaster oven or under broiler until cheese melts and sandwiches are slightly browned.

title: taco salad
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon gelatin mixture into 4 individual plastic containers or serving dishes. Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: lemon bars
directions: For the crust, mix flour, butter and powdered sugar and pat down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add 1 1/3 cups coconut and nuts.
Cool until thick enough to spread.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: stew
directions: Peel and slice the onion, carrots, celery and potatoes.
Place in baking pan or crock-pot with meat.
Sprinkle dry ingredients over meat and vegetables.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover and bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add water and vinegar.
Cook on medium heat until thick about 10 minutes.
Add salt, butter and beets. Cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: milk gravy
directions: Stir butter and milk together.
Add flour to preferred thickness.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix and bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: creamed chipped beef (s~o~s)
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add snipped beef.
Add flour and pepper (will be pasty).
Stir in milk; cook together until bubbly and gravy consistency.
Serve over toast (this is 1 serving). Double for 2 servings, etc.

title: chickpeas and pasta
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add onion and cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until tender, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add garlic and cook 1 minute longer.
Add chickpeas, oregano, black pepper, hot red pepper and bay leaf.
Cook, stirring and crushing half the chickpeas, with back of spoon until heated through, 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes with juice.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat, stirring and breaking up tomatoes with the side of a spoon. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: guiltless scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine first four ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in applesauce; cut until crumbly.
Add honey, egg white and vanilla and mix.
Add fruit and mix. Gradually add 1 tablespoon a time, the yogurt, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Dough should be lumpy and cling to bowl and spoon.
Place dough on greased cookie sheet, forming each scone similar to that of a biscuit, round, about 3 to 4-inches in diameter.
Cook until golden brown.
Scones will have a muffin texture.
Makes 8 to 10 scones.

title: low-fat chicken
directions: You will also need an electric skillet with tight fitting lid.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar.
Chill.
Make into small balls.
Chill again.
Melt paraffin and set aside. Stir in kisses and chocolate chips until dissolved.
Dip peanut butter balls into chocolate mixture.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour over cukes and onion rings.
Chill until cukes are wilted.
(Note:
Low calorie and low-fat.)

title: blueberry-peach cobbler
directions: Drain and wash berries.
In bowl, combine first 3 ingredients and cut in butter; stir in nuts.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, combine the rest of ingredients and spoon the first mixture over.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can be served with ice cream.

title: sloppy joe wagon wheels
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Meanwhile in large skillet cook beef, green pepper and onion until meat is no longer pink, drain.
Stir in the spaghetti sauce and sloppy joe sauce; heat through.
Drain pasta and mix with beef mixture.
Serves 8.

title: low-fat banana split cake
directions: Coat bottom of 13 x 9 pan with vegetable spray. Mix cracker crumbs with water and enough vegetable spray to moisten, then spread on bottom of pan. Beat together 1 carton Cool Whip and cream cheese. Spread over crumbs. Slice bananas on top and add crushed pineapple over bananas. Spread remaining Cool Whip over this and garnish with nuts, cherries and chocolate syrup.

title: cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Stir in melted butter.
Reserve 1/3 cup of crumbs.
Pat the remaining crumbs into pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Form into balls and place on a cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bourbon wienies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,	except	wieners
in a saucepan. Bring to	a boil.
Add sausages and simmer for several minutes before transferring to chafing dish.
Tasty!

title: stuffed celery rings
directions: Clean celery, trimming tops and bottom.
Dry.
Mix cheese, shrimp, cayenne and lemon juice well.
Take a rib of celery and fill with mixture; set aside.
Do this to all ribs.
Press the ribs together with the mixture to the inside, one at a time.
Tie securely with string and refrigerate until firm.
Slice into 1/2-inch rounds.
Put on a lettuce lined dish.
Yield: 8 to 12 servings.

title: teenager's lasagna(serves 6)
directions: Cook noodles 12 to 15 minutes.
Cook beef, onions and garlic until beef is browned.
Turn down heat and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce, paste, mushrooms, salt and oregano.
Combine eggs, spinach, cottage cheese and layer in a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Pour half tomato sauce in bottom.
Cover with half of the noodles.
Top with all the spinach mixture.
Cover with rest of the noodles.
Top with remaining tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with olives; cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil. Cover with cheese slices and bake another 15 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening with sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts, beating after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry; fold into batter.
Pour batter into greased tube pan.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Can add 1 to 1 1/2 cups of fruit or nuts.

title: refrigerator  bran  muffins
directions: Mix the bran with boiling water and let stand while mixing the sugar and shortening with mixer.
Add and combine the buttermilk. Add lightly beaten eggs, mix and then add remaining dry ingredients.
Add raisins or dates if used.
Bake in well greased muffin tins 15 to 18 minutes.
Batter will keep a month or longer in the refrigerator.

title: horseradish salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 8-10 ice cubes to hasten cooling.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine the Eagle Brand milk, mayonnaise, cottage cheese, pineapple and the horseradish.

title: fillet of sole in sherry wine
directions: Stuff fillets of sole with chopped shrimp and onions.
Make sauce of butter, flour and sherry wine.
Pour over top of fillets arranged side by side in greased 8-inch baking dish with cover. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: better 'n fried chicken
directions: Remove skin and all visible fat from chicken.
Put all ingredients in plastic with chicken pieces and shake.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: oreo delight
directions: Mix ingredients
well.	Pour
in
a pan and stick it in the freezer overnight.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in large Dutch oven pan; add noodles to butter. Put burner on high.
Stir noodles constantly until browned. remove from burner.
Add chicken broth and small amount pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Return to burner.
Bring to a boil. After mixture is boiling add rice.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover pan.
Stir occasionally.
Rice pilaf is ready when most of chicken broth is absorbed.

title: best ever carrot cake
directions: Beat together corn oil, sugar and eggs until well combined. In a bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to egg-sugar mixture, mixing well. Drain the pineapple well.
Add carrots, walnuts and pineapple to mixture. Blend to mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 or 10-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cake cool on rack. Prepare frosting. Split cake into 2 layers.
Assemble. Cover with the frosting.
Sprinkle with the coconut.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, line bottom with tortillas, then layer chicken pieces, onions and remaining liquid mixture combined with seasoning.
Cover with cheese and bake in moderate oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: ham and cheese bread(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and half of cheese.
Pour batter into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and sesame seed. Bake 5 minutes more.
Cut into wedges.
Serve warm.
Good with salad and soup.

title: possum
directions: Possum is
very fat and you should place skinned possum in cold water	for a few minutes and scrape real good.
Remove all glands and	put in pan and cover with salt water and leave in refrigerator
overnight.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all the ingredients up to the coconut. Mix in sugar and chill. Right before serving, add coconut, then red and green cherries. Very pretty for Christmas and good tasting.

title: wilma's chili
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Turn into kettle and heat on high to boiling, stirring
constantly.
Reduce
heat to medium and simmer until done, about 1/2 hour.	Stir frequently.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Grease 8-quart bowl with oleo and fill with unsalted popped corn.
Allow enough room to mix.
Mix ingredients in sauce; cook to 250°.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well. Shape with buttered hands into balls.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in a bowl and cover with Saran Wrap, leaving an opening.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes. Take out and stir.
Return back to microwave for 5 minutes, leaving opening in Saran Wrap.
Let stand about 20 minutes or until cool. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and nuts, if desired and 1 teaspoon butter. Beat well with mixer until starts to thicken.
Place in a 9 x 6-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Add Prego sauce and simmer a few minutes.
Cook noodles; drain and cool.
In another bowl, mix egg and cottage cheese.
In bottom of pan, cover with hamburger and meat Prego sauce.
Add noodles, cottage cheese mixture, Monterey Jack cheese and Colby cheese.
Add hamburger meat and sauce. Layer with noodles and cheese again and add meat and sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: low-fat cherry delight
directions: Drain the crushed pineapple in a colander for at least an hour. In a bowl, mix the drained pineapple, cherry pie filling and sweetened condensed milk together. Mix in the whipped topping. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve. Makes 10 servings (about 3/4 cup each).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Make golf ball size cookies.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: stained-glass salad
directions: Mix each flavor of gelatin (according to box directions), but use 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Set in shallow pan or glass dish, so small squares can be cut after the gelatin is set firm.

title: date fingers
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, egg, dates and nuts.
Bring slowly to a boiling point.
Turn to low and allow to cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Cool and shape into small portions about the size of a little finger.
Roll in fine grated coconut.
I dye the coconut red and green for the holidays.

title: brownies
directions: Add baking powder and salt to flour and sift.
Add butter and chocolate and mix well. Melt butter and chocolate together.
Add sugar gradually to eggs; beat thoroughly, then add chocolate to mixture and blend.
Add flour to sugar and mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and margarine in a pan. Beat in sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients plus nuts.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly and frost.

title: chili chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Cook chicken, onion, bell pepper and garlic in oil in Dutch oven until chicken loses its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 45 minutes.
Ladle into bowls and top with cheese, onion, avocado, sour cream or picante.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Add jellos to water and bring to boil; dissolve stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in berries; add cranberry sauce and put in your serving
bowl.
Gently add Sprite; chill overnight and add topping.

title: chocolate cool dessert
directions: Melt flour, margarine, sugar and chopped pecans together and spread evenly in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: quick mayonnaise rolls
directions: Place cup of milk in a mixing bowl.
Add four tablespoons of mayonnaise.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add two cups of flour, gradually. Prepare greased muffin tins.
Spoon in batter.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Combine nuts, dates, baking soda and salt in a mixing bowl. Add the boiling water and shortening and allow this mixture to stand for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly and add to mixture along with the vanilla, sugar and sifted flour.
Add dates to the mixture.
Do not overmix; place in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven or until done.
(A toothpick stuck in the center and coming out clean is an indication that it is done.)

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine chicken, soups and broth.
Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Spray a 10 x 14-inch casserole dish with a nonstick spray.
Layer the following in the casserole dish:
1/2 chicken mixture, 1/2 celery and onion mixture and 1/2 spaghetti.
Layer again; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix with sugar and Crisco, add eggs and vanilla.
Shape into rolls on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until cold.
Slice and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: my mom's bran rolls(clara kockman)
directions: Let first five ingredients stand until lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and knead.
Cover dough.
Let rise until doubled.
(This is actually a refrigerated dough so it can be kept overnight or until ready to use.) Form into rolls and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
May be brushed lightly with Crisco when taken from oven.

title: lemon rice
directions: Grate lemon and set aside.
Squeeze lemon and combine 3 tablespoons juice with rice, water and salt.
Cook according to rice directions.
Garnish with lemon rind.
This is good with Friday night fish and shrimp suppers.

title: beer bread
directions: Melt butter.
Pour 1/2 of this into loaf pan.
Mix flour, sugar and beer.
Spoon flour, sugar, beer mixture into loaf pan. Pour remaining butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: baked chow mein
directions: Cover rice with hot water; let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Brown meat, breaking up large pieces.
When partially browned, add onion, celery and mushrooms.
Stir in brown sugar, soy sauce, water chestnuts and rice.
Turn into lightly greased casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
This serves 8 generously.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Replace green bean juice with fresh water.
Layer all ingredients in casserole (rice on bottom, green beans next, then chicken and water, soup and sherry poured over all).
Bake, uncovered, 2 hours at 350°.

title: pizza crust
directions: Turn oven on to 150° to 200°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add sugar, salt and oil.
Add 2 cups of flour.
Mix until smooth. As you are mixing, mix approximately 1 1/2 cups additional flour. Knead until smooth.
Place in Pam sprayed bowl.
Grease top.
Turn off oven.
Place dough in oven for 30 to 45 minutes to raise. Spread in pizza pan; add sauce and favorite toppings.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Add cheese until melted.
Serve.
Makes one crust.
Double recipe for two.

title: chardy's dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat, beat, beat.
Cold cheese dip.
Also freezes well.

title: green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fold in 1 package of frozen chopped broccoli (thawed).
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or longer, until cheese bubbles to tops and browns.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Mix egg with parmesan cheese in a separate bowl. Stir into spaghetti. Cook hamburger and onion and drain. Add Spaghetti sauce to hamburger and onion. Add spaghetti. Pour into baking dish. Top with pepperoni and mozzarella cheese. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: yogurt cup
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle in water 1 teaspoon at a time, stirring until dough forms.
Press 3 tablespoons of dough into bottom and up the sides of 4 ungreased 6 ounce custard cups to 1/2-inch of top.
Bake until brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Carefully remove cups and allow to cool completely on wire rack. Fill each cup with 1/3 cup of yogurt; garnish with fresh fruit.

title: lemon lush
directions: In a small saucepan, melt margarine; add flour and nuts. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash sweet potatoes.

To 4 cups of mashed potatoes, add 1/4 cup butter, 2 teaspoons salt, orange rind, 1/4 cup brown sugar and enough orange juice to make them light and fluffy. Pour into a baking dish, cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until heated through.
Remove cover. Top with a little marshmallow cream and allow to brown.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cream together.
Add and mix well eggs, vanilla and water.
Then add flour, salt and soda and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and pecans; mix.
Add oats and mix. Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Use a heaping tablespoonful for large cookies.
Makes 3 dozen.
Bake at 350° no longer than 10 minutes.
Will seem soft, but will get firm as they cool.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Saute onion
in
small	amount of grease in frying pan. Crumble hamburger
meat
into frying pan and brown while stirring. Add can
of tomato soup and kidney beans.	Add salt and chili powder to taste.
If too thick add water.
Heat through.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs. Add butter and cream. Add enough flour to make dough thick.
Knead lightly to make smooth. Roll flat with rolling pin.
Roll dough to form one long roll and cut. Lay cut pieces flat on floured surface and let set for 1 to 2 hours.
Cook in chicken broth.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in small amount of water until soft. Drain.
Mash squash and add butter and beaten eggs.
Mix well, then add crumbs and milk and blend thoroughly.
Add some of the cheese and mix in salt and pepper to taste.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix well and put into a Pyrex baking bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta marinade
directions: Note:
May add crabmeat, shrimp or cooked cut up chicken breast pieces to salad.

title: chuck wagon casserole(serves 8)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Add topping.

title: pecan millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler.
Add 3 tablespoons of water. Add chopped pecans.
Let cool and when candy will hold its shape on spoon, drop by spoonful on buttered cookie sheet.
Let set until firm.
Melt Hershey bars and paraffin and dip caramel drops until coated.

title: chicken tetrazzini(low-fat and cholesterol)
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over medium heat; add mushrooms and onion and saute 7 minutes or until liquid evaporates. Stir in all-purpose flour.
Gradually add chicken broth, skim milk and light processed cream cheese product; bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and next 5 ingredients.
Stir spaghetti and chicken into mushroom mixture.
Spoon mixture into a deep 3-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 servings (about 339 calories per 1 1/3 cup servings).
Protein 26.6, fat 7.1, carbohydrate 40.7, cholesterol 46, iron 2.8, sodium 417 and calcium 181.

title: giant popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter or spray 9 (6 ounce) cups. Arrange on cookie sheet.
With mixer on low, beat eggs slightly. Add in milk and melted butter.
Beat until blended, then gradually beat in flour and salt.
Pour into cups to 1/4-inch of top.
Bake 60 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Quickly cut slit in side of each. Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Outstanding; serve with prime rib.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put into a baked pie crust and top with whipping cream.

title: onion casserole
directions: Wilt onions in butter.
Spray Pam in a casserole dish; put 1/2 cracker crumbs, 1/2 of onions and 1/2 mushroom soup; then another layer of each.
Beat egg and add to milk.
Pour over top of casserole and add butter to top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring water and jello to a good boil.
Thicken with cornstarch, remove from fire and hand beat.
Let cool briefly, then add fresh strawberries and serve with Cool Whip.

title: mama's pork chop dumplings
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet.
Add 1/2 cup water and sliced onion.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, approximately 50 minutes.
Drain off excess fat and additional water.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Melt margarine and saute onion until clear.
Mix all ingredients well and place in well-greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes, onion and salt with boiling water and cook 5 minutes.
