Place in small greased casserole.
Add pepper and cheese to white sauce.
Pour over potatoes. Top with crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: hash brown potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat together eggs and milk; stir in potatoes, green onions, salt.
Stir in 1 cup of the cheese and half of bacon.
Pour into greased 9 inch pie plate or quiche dish. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until center is set.
Sprinkle remaining bacon and cheese over top; continue baking 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Fry sausage until crumbly.
Remove from skillet.
Add to skillet drippings the onion, pepper and celery; saute until tender, but not brown.
Place in a baking dish the rice, almonds, sausage, sauteed vegetables, broth and water.
Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and stir.
May need to cook for an additional 10 minutes.

title: tater crisp chicken
directions: To change flavor or spice it up, use seasoned salt, cajun spice or Mrs. Dash.
In place of salt, paprika, tarragon, basil, marjoram or thyme may be added to potato mixture.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil cut up eggplant until soft.
Drain and mash.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Save some grated cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake in casserole dish at 400° until thickened.

title: spiced waldorf salad
directions: Place red cinnamon candies and 1 cup water in a saucepan. Heat until candies are dissolved.
Add cherry jello, stirring until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened. Then fold in chopped nuts.
Mold and chill in mold.
Garnish with crisp greens or mayonnaise or a creamy dressing.

title: prune nut bread
directions: Combine prunes, orange peel and juice.
Let stand 1/2 hour. Sift together dry ingredients.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over nuts and dates, let stand.
Mix with mixer shortening and sugar, break in eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add soda to nuts and dates mixture.
(Do not do earlier or dates will turn red.)
Mix by hand.
Stir in flour and fruit mixture, alternately.
Gently add to the shortening mixture.
Then add 2/3 cup water and mix gently, beat well.
Makes 4 small pans.
Oil and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 300° and bake for 45 minutes more.
May substitute pumpkin or squash for carrots.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry fluff(low-fat and sugar-free)
directions: Thaw fruit; set aside.
Boil 1 1/2 cups water.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Refrigerate. Prepare Featherweight according to package directions.
When Jell-O is almost set, whip at high speed until fluffy.
Fold together fruit, topping and Jell-O.
Chill until set.
Serves 16.

title: sweet sour rigatoni
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Blend all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in bran which has been soaked in milk for 5 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring to moisten.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 11 large muffins.

title: bulgarian mexican salad
directions: Place cabbage in bowl, mix it with salt and vinegar/lemon juice. Add remainder of ingredients and mix well. This is better served cold after several hours.

title: christmas ball
directions: Mix.
Chill.
Wet hands and roll into ball.
Roll in parsley on waxed paper.
Top with artificial poinsettia.

title: pastor's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Put sugar in mixing bowl.
Fold in margarine or butter.
Fold in cream cheese.
Add 1 egg at a time, folding each in before adding another.
Sift flour and add a small amount at a time.
Add a pinch of salt and vanilla.
Mix on high speed for about 2 minutes.
Place into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Place in cold oven; bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours, depending on oven.

title: baked beans with beef and bacon
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper.
Partially cook bacon; set aside.
(May cook bacon 1 1/2 minutes in microwave.) Stir all ingredients together; pour into pan, placing bacon on top.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef and sausage lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef and sausage with garlic and onion in olive oil in skillet.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, seasonings and 1 cup water; mix well.
Simmer, covered, for 2 to 3 hours.
Alternate layers of sauce, noodles, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese in large shallow baking dish until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: congealed strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: Mix gelatin and pineapple in a large saucepan.
Do not boil. Allow to cool.
Mix in buttermilk, pecans and whipped topping until blended.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch oblong dish or clear glass bowl.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Blend onion, bell pepper, soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes in blender. Place layer of chips, cheese and chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; pour 1/2 of soup mixture over. Repeat layers, ending with soup mixture. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: chili baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish or microwave dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 400° in conventional oven or microwave on High 12 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and put in casserole dish.
Add the carrots that have been
sliced.
Put
on
top of potatoes. Add celery.
Drain green peas and onion slices.
This is layer by layer.
Add salt
and
pepper
to
taste.
Cook
hamburger slightly and add on top of onion.
Take the liquid drained off peas and pour over.
Add can of tomatoes.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy potato gratin
directions: Peel the potatoes, dropping into a bowl of cold water to cover.
Slice potatoes into 1/8 to 1/4 inch strips.
Place in a bowl of cold water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°. Heavily butter a shallow 2 to 3-quart gratin dish or 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Dry potatoes well with paper towels.
Overlap half the potatoes in lengthwise rows in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and half the cheese.
Repeat with second layer of potatoes.
Pour 3/4 cup cream over the top. Bake uncovered at 375° for 40 minutes.
If serving immediately, continue baking for 20 minutes more, until top is golden brown and potatoes are tender.
(Gratin may be baked for 40 minutes, then covered and held at room temperature for up to 3 hours.
Pour 1/4 cup cream over the top and return to oven for 20 minutes, uncovered.)

title: dutch oven roast
directions: Melt fat in Dutch oven; add meat and brown well on all sides. Add water, salt and diced onion; cover and place in moderate oven at 350° and cook for 2 hours.
Add prepared vegetables; cover and cook another hour or until meat forks tender and vegetables are done.

title: potato poupon
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and microwave at 50% power for about 4 minutes.
Stir.
Place half of potatoes in a sprayed casserole dish; add half of sauce.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
If desired, sprinkle grated cheese on top for the last 5 to 10 minutes or baking.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Mix well and roll like biscuits 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Grease cookie sheet.
Stack 2 deep with margarine between layers.
Grease tops with margarine.
Let rise until double in size, about 2 or 3 hours.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar and soda.
Add vinegar, vanilla and flour.
Mix together.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 300° oven.
Do not flatten cookies.

title: quick yeast muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside.
Melt margarine and cream with sugar.
Add yeast and beaten egg.
Gradually add flour. Stir until well mixed.
Spoon mixture into greased muffin pans, filling two-thirds full.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: simply delicious
directions: Line 9 x 13 pan with ice cream sandwiches.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top and sprinkle pecans over syrup.
Soften 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream and spread over nuts.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over ice cream and sprinkle pecans on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: homemade honey baked ham
directions: Three days in advance, mix ingredients in small saucepan. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Set aside.
Trim visible fat from ham. Take an ice pick and punch holes all over the entire ham as deep as possible.
Marinate ham with sauce every 3 to 4 hours the first two days.
Don't forget to turn it over.
On the third day, you only need to marinate twice.
Smoke on covered grill at lowest setting for two hours.
Keep an eye on it so it doesn't burn.

title: roasted potatoes with parmesan cheese
directions: Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag.
Moisten potatoes with water coating each potato well with cheese mixture.
Melt butter in large baking pan (9 x 13-inch pan works well).
Put potatoes in single layers in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning potatoes halfway through baking time.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths and coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
In a saucepan, melt margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon. Place 1/2 of the biscuits in a greased Bundt pan.
Add 1/2 cup pecans and raisins.
Pour 1/2 of the melted mixture over this. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry soda
directions: Mix all ingredients except cherry drink in blender on medium speed.
Pour mixture into 2 large glasses.
Pour 3 ounces cherry flavored soda over top of each.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, flour and sugar well.
Add milk, margarine, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Stir Jell-O into cottage cheese until dissolved. Add Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry and pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Fold in zucchini, nuts, pineapple and cherries.
Put into 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: texas hominy grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in 6 cups water as package directs.
Do not add salt.
Add butter, cheese, eggs, savory salt and Tabasco sauce. Mix well.

title: jane's chili(good!)
directions: Put beans in 9 cups of water with 1 teaspoon of salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce to simmer and cook for 1 3/4 hours.
Save 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Cook meat with vegetables until they are tender. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; simmer for 3 hours.
You can use a crock-pot, if desired.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: rotini salad
directions: Mix all above together refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken nuggets with pineapple sauce
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour, eggs, water and salt in small bowl. Stir well.
Cover and chill batter 1 hour.
Dip chicken in chilled batter, dredge in remaining 1 cup flour.
Fry 4 to 5 pieces of chicken at a time in hot peanut oil (375°) in a large skillet or wok until golden.
Drain well on paper towels.
Serve warm with pineapple sauce.
Yield:
9 appetizer servings.

title: peppermint bark
directions: Line an 11 x 17-inch baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside. In the top of a double boiler or a metal bowl set over a pot of simmering water, melt the white chocolate, stirring constantly. With a chef's knife or hammer, cut or pound candy canes into 1/4-inch pieces. Stir candy cane pieces and peppermint oil into the melted chocolate. Remove from the heat and pour the mixture into the prepared baking sheet and spread evenly. Chill until firm, 25 to 30 minutes. Break into pieces. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Grease baking dish.
Pour rice into dish.
Slowly add 2 cups water.
Place salt and peppered chicken on top of rice.
Pour mushroom soup over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil.
Pour over remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar and baking soda.
Make 3 holes and put in vinegar and melted margarine.
Mix with fork.
Then add 2 cups of water.
Mix.
Make a layer or large pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs and butter. Place in dish.
Top with melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup, ground beef, crumbs, egg, onion and 1/2 each of seasonings.
Shape into 6 mini loaves.
Brown in shortening.
Drain. Pour on remaining soup, seasonings and water. Cover and cook on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine.
Add crushed crackers, saving 1/4 for the top. Press mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk and pudding.
Add ice cream and Cool Whip.
Mix well with mixer.
Pour over crumbs and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Pour in 2 jars pizza sauce.
Heat through.
Cook noodles until tender; drain.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put a spoonful of hamburger sauce.
Layer with 3 noodles.
Cover with sauce.
Layer cheese.
Continue layering until used up.
Pour third jar of pizza sauce over top.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool; cut in pieces.
Serve.

title: apricot glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots and 1 teaspoon salt until carrots are tender. Melt margarine; stir in preserves. Add 1/4 teaspoon salt, nutmeg, orange juice and rind. Cook 5 minutes. Add carrots and toss.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash seeds well.
Mix 1 quart water to 1/2 cup salt.
Add seeds.
Let boil about 3 minutes.
Drain off water.
Roast seeds slowly on a baking sheet for about 2 1/2 hours at 250°.
Turn occasionally.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the beaten egg.
Sift in the flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix with the sour milk.
Add the blueberries.
Pour into an 8 x8-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with a thick layer of cinnamon-sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Put meat in the mixture and marinate overnight.
Check every few hours to be sure chicken is covered with mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Combine the bread crumbs and parsley on a plate.
Place the cheese on another plate.
In a small bowl, lightly beat the egg whites with water.
Dip the chicken into the cheese, then into the egg whites, then into the crumb mixture.
Lay them on a rack and refrigerate, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Add all ingredients together in a 4-quart stock pot and cook for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Bring to a boil the water, sugar and butter.
Remove from heat.
Then add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until dissolved and mixture is smooth. Beat in 2 eggs, one at a time.
Add to flour mixture gradually. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: apple yum yums!
directions: Unroll and separate crescents; slice in half making 32 triangles. Place 3 to 4 apple slices on widest point of crescent and roll up. Stand rolls on end in 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Pour orange juice in pan around rolls. Drizzle with margarine. Mix cinnamon, sugar and 1 teaspoon orange rind grated together. Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine onions, cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk, then coat with cheese mixture.
Place in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/4-inch baking dish.
Pour oleo over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet tooth chess cake
directions: Mix 1 egg, stick of butter and cake mix until crumbly.
Press in bottom of 28 x 18-inch (large) cake pan.
Mix until creamy 3 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over crumb mixture. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: nutty buddy pie
directions: Blend together cream cheese, milk, confectioners sugar and peanut butter.
Next fold in two large Cool Whip; pour into chocolate pie crust.
Makes 3 pies.
Melt chocolate chips and drizzle on pies.
You can also put coconut, peanuts, chocolate chips or chocolate syrup on top, then freeze and eat.

title: polenta - by microwave
directions: Put all in a large pot, about 3-quart.
Stir and cover. Microwave on High 7 to 10 minutes.
Add 4 tablespoons butter. Stir until melted.
Put back in microwave about 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat sugar and shortening until fluffy. Add eggs, pumpkin and water; mix well.
Stir in flour mixture and nuts.
Turn into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 - 60 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans. Cool completely.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Next fold in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After cake has been removed from pan, it can be sprinkled with powdered sugar for decoration or glazed.

title: chicken curry with two onions(murgh do piaza; serves 4)
directions: Combine spices with yogurt and lemon juice.
Clean chicken and remove all skin and fat.
Dry chicken.
Cover chicken pieces with yogurt mixture.
Marinate at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together like pie dough.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
Add egg, milk and soda.
Pour into pan.
Put reserved crumbs on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: In mixing bowl, place cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Blend well at medium speed.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in 1/2 cup of chocolate chips.
Pour batter into pie crust.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or more.

title: aunt flowie's chocolate cake
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients.
Let cool in pan.
Put remaining ingredients in a large bowl, then add chocolate.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Test with toothpick.
Do not overbake.
When cool, frost with Chocolate Icing.

title: mexican eggs
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in margarine.
Add sliced mushrooms and tomato (crushed).
Cook until tomato and mushrooms are heated through.
Mix eggs together in separate dish and add to onion and tomato mixture.
Cook together, mixing all ingredients together until eggs are cooked through.

title: broccoli-spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and spinach.
Make sure it's completely drained.
Mix soup, onion, mayo, eggs, spinach and broccoli together.
Butter casserole dish.
Pour in mixture and top with cheese, then with crackers. Dab top with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Combine chicken, chiles, onion, soup, broth, mushrooms and green pepper.
Butter tortillas and cut each in half.
Spread 12 of the halves in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread half the chicken mixture on top.
Sprinkle on half of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake one hour at 325°.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening together and add eggs and well drained pineapple (saving the juice).	Sift dry ingredients together and add, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
After removing from oven, spread lightly with a thin icing made from the reserved pineapple juice and confectioners sugar.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and place juice aside.
Tear into bite size angel food cake and place in large plastic container (with sealed top).
Pour 2 tablespoons pineapple juice over bite size angel food cake.
Mix or shake pudding and 3 cups skim milk until it is well mixed. Add 1/2 cup pineapple juice, chunky pineapple and sour cream to pudding mix. Stir well.
Pour over cake and top with Cool Whip.
Place pineapple slices on top.
Let sit overnight.

title: cream puffs and vanilla pastry cream
directions: Heat until boiling:
butter, water and salt.
Remove from heat and add flour and baking powder.
Stir vigorously until dough forms a ball.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, blending completely each time.
Cool overnight in fridge.
Bring to room temperature before baking.
Make 12 round mounds on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for around 45 minutes.
Remove and cut slit on side of each cream puff; bake for 10 more minutes.
Turn off oven and let sit 10 more minutes.
Cool and fill with cream.
Drizzle with chocolate.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Debone fryer and cook gumbo mix, celery, onion and tomatoes in 6 cups chicken broth or water for 45 to 60 minutes on medium heat; then add chicken.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix apples, apple juice concentrate, thickener and spice. Stir until apples are well coated.
Add lemon juice to keep apples light colored.
Taste 1 piece of apple to check spice.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Top with 2nd crust or pastry strips.
Seal edges.
Cut slits into top crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake in 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: green pea layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a 3-quart oblong, shallow dish. Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together meal, salt, soda, milk, corn, cheese and peppers. Pour hot bacon grease in bottom of pan.
Pour batter into pan (iron skillet is best).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: streusel topping
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In a medium-sized bowl, stir together flour, brown sugar and butter until crumbly.
Add pecans and stir; set aside.

title: cinnamon ring
directions: Sprinkle chopped walnuts in greased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Dip biscuits in butter, then sugar mixture. Place in pan, overlapping slightly.
Tuck raisins in between biscuits.
Add any remaining sugar mixture and butter.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Invert pan.
Serve warm.

title: smith's zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.

title: sensational stuffed shells
directions: Cook vegetables in oil in skillet until tender-crisp.
Stir in flour and milk; cook until thickened.
Remove from heat; add cottage cheese, 2 tablespoons Parmesan and salt and pepper.
Stuff shells and place in shallow baking dish.
Top with remaining Parmesan.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 25 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: spicy apple blueberry crunch(microwave dessert)
directions: Place apples and blueberries in a microwave-safe 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the dry pudding mix.
Set aside.

title: cream cheese roll ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, green onions, cheese, and salad dressing. Spread over tortillas and roll up.
Cut into smaller pieces and serve.

title: onion potato bake
directions: Lay chopped potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine onion soup and melted margarine; mix well.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Pour in milk.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water. Add seasonings and broccoli.

title: wedding rice
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Crunch up vermicelli pasta into approximately 1-inch lengths.
Saute pasta in butter until golden brown.
Add chicken broth to butter and vermicelli.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and cover; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add toasted almonds, chopped dates and coconut to rice.
Continue to simmer for 10 more minutes.
Remove rice from stove.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetable casserole(great for potluck suppers; kids like this one!)
directions: Thaw Brussels sprouts.
Layer all the vegetables in a large casserole or crock-pot.
Yellow beans on the bottom and creamed corn on the top works best.
Spread cheese around top of casserole and top off with the pimento. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or on low in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.

title: hot chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler, or over very low heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve hot over ice cream. May be stored in covered jar and reheated when needed.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° until done.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Blend remaining ingredients; add chocolate mixture.
Do not beat.
(May add 1/2 cup pecans.)
Pour into cups.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick tomato sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pot over medium low heat until blended.
Turn heat to medium and stir occasionally.
The sauce is done in 45 minutes.

title: rhonda's broccoli burgers(vegetarian recipe)
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs to blend.
Stir in broccoli, almonds, onion, bread crumbs and water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in boiling salted water until tender. Drain and mash until smooth.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, pepper and salts and beat until light and fluffy.
Place potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Swirl potato mixture with back of a spoon to make a circular or meringue-like pattern.
Sprinkle with paprika and run briefly under the broiler.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into a bowl; add shortening.
Mix well with fork; add milk.
Knead slightly.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cutter.
Bake on greased baking sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs until well mixed. Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until browned. (You can also bake this in a 13 x 9 pan.)

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add water and vanilla; mix well. Gradually add flour. Fold in pecans. Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheets and flatten with fingers. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes. (I had to bake for 30 minutes.) Cool on wire rack. When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: stir and roll biscuits
directions: Combine in mixing bowl and stir quickly until dough clings together.
Turn quickly onto floured board.
Roll out and cut out with biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake about 10 minutes at 450°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in the oleo. Add corn and Cheez Whiz. Stir until mixed. Add rice and put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Can cook in microwave for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix lemon gelatin, hot water and juice of lemon until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar; add vanilla.
Combine gelatin mixture and cheese.
Whip chilled Milnot and fold into mixture, gently.
Pour over graham cracker crust. Chill (better if made the day before).
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix together salad dressing, cream cheese and dry mix.
Pat crescent rolls in bottom of cookie sheet pan with sides.
Prick a little and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
After crust cools, spread with cream cheese-salad dressing mixture.
Top with whatever you want such as: celery, broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, green onion, grated carrots, radishes, mushrooms and olives.
Then top with grated mild Cheddar cheese.
Chill.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except tortillas).
Spread on tortilla shells.
Roll each shell and chill.
Slice when chilled enough.
Serve with chili sauce.

title: nana's cream cake
directions: With electric mixer beat eggs until foamy, add sugar and vanilla and continue to beat for 2 minutes.
Blend in cream and other additional liquid by hand.
Add flour and continue to mix by hand slowly until well blended.
Beat 1/2 minute with electric mixer on low speed.
Bake in a loaf pan, that has been greased and floured, at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: banana-strawberry mold
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all in a bowl!
Put one-half in Pyrex glass pan.
When jelled (cool), spread pint sour cream on top.
Then cover with remaining mixture.
Refrigerate to set!

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix all
ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil broth; add 1 cube chicken bouillon until dissolved.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Cook until boiling.
Pour over cut-up chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine Bisquick and milk. Mix. Drop on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Stir in vegetables, rice, soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Turn in shallow 2-quart baking dish. Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until rice is tender.
Top with noodles and bake 2 minutes longer.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Drop in tube cake pan.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and butter.
Beat well and add eggs, one at a time, blending in well.
Add vanilla and salt.
Continue beating and slowly add milk.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown ground chuck, sausage and smoked sausage.
Boil chicken and cool and debone (save stock).
Saute bell peppers, chopped green onions, onions and celery.
Add meat, chopped chicken, sauteed vegetables, creole seasoning and Kitchen Bouquet to 5 cups uncooked rice and 10 cups water or stock.
Bring to boil then reduce heat to low setting stirring occasionally until rice is tender.
Bon appetit!!

title: holiday cheese log
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix with other ingredients. Roll in paprika or chili powder.
Chill until firm.
Slice and serve.
Serves about 16.

title: molasses-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream molasses, sugar and shortening until smooth.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add raisins and nuts; mix well.
Add dry ingredients, sifted.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: spicy ground beef casserole
directions: Cook shells and cheese; set aside.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer ground beef, corn, green beans and tomatoes.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Combine brown sugar, dry mustard, flour, salt, pepper, boiling water and vinegar.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add raisins and cook 5 minutes longer. Add margarine and serve over ham.

title: tea scones
directions: Place flour in a bowl.
Rub in butter.
Add baking powder, sugar and raisins; mix well.
Beat egg and add to milk; reserve 1 tablespoon of the mixture.
Add remainder to dry ingredients. Knead to make moist dough.
Turn onto a well floured board; roll 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch rounds with biscuit cutter or inverted glass.
Arrange on slightly floured baking sheet.
Brush tops with reserve egg mixture.
Bake at 425° until risen and lightly browned, about 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Avoid overbaking.

title: cheese delights
directions: Toast rounds of bread the size of tomato slices.
Spread with crisp, chopped bacon, blended with mayonnaise.
Top with tomato slice, cucumber slice and stuffed olive slice.

title: salmon puffs
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk and soup; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until appears set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese supreme
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown beef, onion and celery.
Pour excess fat off.
Stir in tomato sauce and meat mixture with macaroni and pour into two-quart casserole.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: honey butter
directions: Put in blender.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Chill well. Will be spreading consistency.

title: rob's steak
directions: Marinate for 30 minutes in a bowl in refrigerator. Heat grill to optimum temperature. Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper. Place on grill and cook until outside is dark/black and inside is slightly pink.
Eat.

title: royal raisin sauce
directions: Simmer raisins in 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Make paste of cornstarch, sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Add paste mixture to raisins and heat until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Serve over ham, pork, ham loaf or gingerbread.

title: chicken for casseroles or salads
directions: Note:
Add salt and pepper at time of serving.
Great for Javanese dinner.

title: fresh corn-on-the-cob in microwave
directions: Discard any soiled outer pieces of husk.
Soak corn in cold water for 5 to 10 minutes to clean and moisten.
Drain well; do not dry.
Set unhusked corn directly on ceramic tray and cook (microwave on High, Maximum power) 11 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes and peel back husks.
Discard silks and recover with husks.
Serve hot with butter and salt.

title: orange chicken
directions: Combine eggs and orange juice.
Dip chicken in mixture and then into mixture of bread crumbs, salt, paprika and shredded orange peel.
In 400° oven, melt butter in a large, shallow baking pan.
Remove pan from oven and turn chicken in butter to coat. Bake 40 minutes.
Cover with foil last 10 minutes.

title: grandma's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, mix flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugars and vanilla. With a wooden spoon, beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes approximately 8 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix Karo and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add salt, flavoring, oleo and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 340°.
Cook for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mother's white fruit cake
directions: Chop fruit and dredge in flour.
Mix remaining ingredients; add fruit.
Pour into a 3 x 5-inch oblong pan (or pan of desirable size).
Bake for 2 to 3 hours at 250°.
Baking time will depend on size and thickness of pan.
Yield:
11 1/2 cups batter.

title: white christmas
directions: Melt candy in heavy kettle or double boiler.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Stir gently and mix well.
Spoon onto waxed papered cookie sheet in heaping teaspoonfuls.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Store in airtight container.
May be refrigerated.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: peggy's baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Either marinate fish in lemon juice or sprinkle lemon on fish before baking.
Put fish in glass baking dish.
Pour soup over it and then sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheeses, then let soften.
Beat cream cheese until creamy and light.
Mix in Cheddar cheeses and dressing mix. Mix until well blended.
Roll into balls, approximately the size of grapefruit.
Roll in chopped pecans to coat.
Makes 2.

title: rosebud rolls
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients well with mixer.
Add the egg, Crisco and flour.
Mix well with mixer.
Let stand 1/2 hour. Spoon into muffin pans. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Crush cookies.
Melt butter.
Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding mix and ice cream (ice cream melted enough to mix).
Let pudding and ice cream filling set (in refrigerator), then top with Cool Whip.
Crush Heath bars (easier if frozen); sprinkle on top.
Put in refrigerator.

title: taco sticks
directions: Follow directions on taco seasoning package to make taco meat. Let cool when finished.
Cut cheese into 3 x 1/4 x 1/4-inch strips.
Lay eggroll wrap with corner facing you.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of taco meat on corner closest to you.
Place one strip of cheese in also.
Baste wrap across from filling with beaten egg.
Roll according to wrap instructions.
Deep fry in oil until cheese starts to come out of wrapper.
Serve with taco or picante sauce for dipping.
Sour cream is optional as a dip.

title: fun jello jigglers
directions: Spray cookie sheet or molds with cooking spray.
Mix boiling water and jello in bowl until all is dissolved.
Pour into pan or mold.
Refrigerate until cool.
You can also use cookie cutters to cut into shapes or cut into squares.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 2 or more large crusts.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs and pumpkin.
Blend in sugar, spice and flour; mix well.
Add milk; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May add pecans to mix.

title: parsley fries and eggs
directions: Heat oil and butter in large skillet. Add cubed potatoes, seasonings and stir well. Fry slowly on medium-low heat until golden brown. Push potatoes to one side and break eggs into skillet. Mix both together when eggs are almost done. Makes 6 servings.

title: fluffy banana cake
directions: Beat on high for 1 1/2 minutes, shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add milk.
Add sifted flour mixture alternately with mashed banana while on medium speed, beat only enough to blend, about 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 layer pans or 1 large pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or fluffy white frosting.

title: lemon basil cookies
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese, egg and lemon juice until well blended and fluffy. Blend in cake mix, 1/3 at a time, mixing last portion by hand. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by level tablespoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Mix all ingredients, including all the juice from canned fruits.
Spoon into parfait glass or small paper cups.
Cover with foil and freeze.
Thaw for 30 minutes before serving.
Keeps in freezer for 1 month or more.

title: deviled liver
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in all ingredients.
Marinate liver 1/2 to 3/4 hour or overnight.
Dip in bread crumbs and fry in bacon grease.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Mix and chill in refrigerator, then serve.

title: chili verde
directions: Lightly brown meat in a large skillet.
Drain.
Transfer to a large stew pot and sprinkle flour over meat.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until pork becomes tender and falls apart, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and serve with warmed flour tortillas or similar bread. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: bean pot
directions: Cook onions and garlic in oil until softened, but not brown. Mix sugar, vinegar, catsup, salt, mustard, pepper and molasses together.
Pour over onion and garlic.
Mix thoroughly and simmer. Add beans.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and cook 1 1/2 hours at 350° or in crock-pot.

title: pineapple cake(this cake is very low-fat without frosting.)
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add pineapple (juice and all), flour, white sugar, brown sugar, baking soda and eggs; mix together.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spread evenly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Frost with Cream Cheese Ginger Frosting.

title: dieters delight salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: Trim fat from bones.
Drain mixed vegetables and green beans. Reserve liquid.
Combine tomato sauce, reserved liquid and enough water to measure 6 cups.
Pour into crock-pot; add beef bones. Cover; cook on low for 4 to 6 hours or until meat falls from bones.
Remove bones; stir in vegetables, herbs, seasonings and noodles.
Cover; cook on low for 2 to 3 hours longer or until noodles are tender.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese.
Fold in good.
Drain pineapple; fold into cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in good.
Chill until ready to serve.
You can also mix in pecans, but it's optional.

title: pork chop rice hot dish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Lay pork chops on top. Sprinkle with onion soup and seal with aluminum foil. Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: ellen's chicken breasts
directions: Spread dried beef over bottom of baking dish.
Wrap chicken breasts with bacon.
Place over beef.
Mix and spoon mushroom soup and sour cream over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 3 hours.

title: caramelized phyllo key lime natilla
directions: Combine whole eggs, yolks, sugar and lime juice in large mixing bowl.
Whisk vigorously over simmering water until mixture is ribbony and pale in color.
Remove from heat and whisk in softened butter.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Whip heavy cream until stiff.
Whisk approximately 1/4 of cream into Key lime mixture to lighten it.
Fold in remaining cream.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites, adding sugar very gradually until mixture is very dry and stiff.
Fold in the Rice Krispies and chocolate bits, mixing well.
On ungreased cookie sheet or parchment drop on pan with a teaspoon.
Place in a preheated 350° oven. Close the door and turn off the oven.
Leave in the oven for 4 hours or overnight. Store in a tin.

title: ginger pear salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into mold (or 9 x 13-inch glass pan) and chill.
Whip cream cheese and ginger in mixer.
Add gelatin and beat until smooth.
Cut up pears and add to mixture.
Pour on top of congealed jello and refrigerate until set.

title: orange zucchini squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in nuts and zucchini.
Add orange juice and oil to beaten egg whites.
Fold in dry ingredients; stir in orange peel.
Spoon dough into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool.
Frost and cut into squares.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool.
Peel and dice potatoes and put in 2-quart baking dish.
Heat margarine and half and half in saucepan until margarine is melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Heat together beets and liquid.
Mix remaining ingredients. Stir into beets.
Cook, stirring constantly until smoothly blended and thickened.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Put in 1 cup uncooked rice, then chicken pieces.
Add celery soup as is.
Sprinkle over the onion soup.
Pour water in dish.
Cut small pieces of butter over top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese ball or ring
directions: Shred cheese.
Combine cheese, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Form into ball or ring.
Roll in pecans.

title: ham and cornbread salad
directions: Make corn muffins; cool and crumble. Add remaining ingredients.

title: baked barley
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and brown well.
Add 1/2 cup slivered almonds, bouillon, pepper and oregano to taste.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check and stir after 1/2 hour.
Mix should be dry in appearance.

title: strawberry oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together sugar and margarine. Mix in eggs, milk, applesauce, lemon juice and lemon peel.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt, then mix in oats.
Slowly add dry ingredients to wet ingredients, mixing well by hand.
Coarsely chop strawberries and add to mixture.
Pour in muffin pans lined with paper cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 20 muffins.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, celery, prepared mustard and 1/2 teaspoon of salt in skillet.
Drain; mix egg, milk, dry mustard, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add to beef.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Place biscuits over mixture.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are done.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Mix all together and cook
in crock-pot 4 to 6 hours.
Put over noodles, rice or spaghetti.

title: easy cranberry sauce(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: oriental seafood dinner
directions: Boil rice in salted water; drain.
Heat vegetables in microwave.
Mix with rice.
Stir in sardines.
Serves 2.
Add soy sauce at the table.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Whip evaporated milk in bowl.
Combine marshmallows, fruit cocktail, pineapple, sugar, cherries and pecans in bowl; mix well. Fold in whipped evaporated milk.
Chill, tightly covered, in refrigerator.
Serve over pound cake.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown sausage and beef.
Drain in colander and blot with paper towel.
Combine with other ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.
Spread on rye bread and freeze individually on waxed paper.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix gelatine and cold water until dissolved; pour mixture into heated soup and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour into buttered mold; refrigerate.

title: chili con queso
directions: Braise beef, drain.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Sizzle until beef has absorbed most of water.
Add diced chiles and pimento, stir.
Add bacon bits to taste.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mash ice cream and pour juice over it.
Add ginger ale and serve.

title: stirrup chocolate cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix until smooth. Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° until cake springs back when touched.

title: diabetic strawberry pie
directions: Bring soda to boil.
Remove from burner; add jello.
Mix well. Add cold water.
Slice fresh fruit to desire.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: plantation tea
directions: Combine boiling water and tea bags and steep for 20 minutes, then add rest of ingredients.

title: congealed carrot salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package, using 1/2 cup less water.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Boil raisins in water 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream sugar and shortening; beat in eggs.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins mixture, then dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: saucy kielbasa
directions: Boil sausage on simmer 15 minutes, drain and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Mix ingredients and put kielbasa and sauce into a roaster, mix.
Bake uncovered for 45-55 minutes at 400°.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix together 1/3 cup
sugar, cinnamon and 1 teaspoon melted butter for topping.

title: pot of gold
directions: Fry hamburger and onion. Add rest of ingredients, except cheese and noodles. Place in casserole pan. Layer mixture with uncooked noodles. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture around each olive, covering completely.
Arrange on baking sheet and freeze until firm.
(Store in freezer bag in freezer.)
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes when ready to serve.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 - 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with Fritos Scoops.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add well-beaten eggs; beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas, beating after each addition until batter is smooth. Turn into buttered bread pan and bake at 350° about 70 minutes.

title: sweet potato sausage stuffing
directions: Peel, slice and boil the sweet potatoes until just tender. Mash them well.
There should be about 6 cups.
Fry the sausage until done, breaking it up with a fork as it cooks.
Remove the sausage.
Saute the onions and celery in the drippings.
Place the mashed sweet potatoes, sausage, celery, onions and drippings in a large bowl.
Add the bread crumbs, raisins, parsley, thyme, sage, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir gently until well mixed.
Add apples (optional).
Use more sweet potatoes or less bread crumbs. Add the nutmeg and mace when using the pecans (optional) or the pecans and apples together.

title: 2 x 4's
directions: Beat together first four ingredients.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into first mixture until all dry ingredients are absorbed.
Add raisins and stir well.
Spread batter into a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Brush with milk and coat well with white sugar.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken italiano
directions: In large skillet, combine chicken and 1/3 of the Italian dressing.
Saute until chicken starts to brown.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing.
Cover; simmer 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Serve over pasta.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Stir in flour, chocolate syrup, vanilla and nuts.
Turn into greased and lightly floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tester inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into 16 squares.
Remove from pan and store airtight.

title: pork and green chili casserole
directions: Stir-fry pork half at a time in hot oil.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Heat and stir just until bubbly.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake until cheese melts.

title: spinat salat(spinach salad)
directions: Wash the spinach well in several changes of clear water.
Cut away the tough stem and discard them.
Drain the spinach leaves and chill in a damp cloth.
Roll a handful of leaves and slice with a very sharp knife into 1/4-inch strips.
Toss the spinach with the dressing and serve on a bed of leaf lettuce; sprinkle the crumbled fried bacon on top.

title: corn fritters
directions: Place in a blender the flour, salt, baking powder, milk and egg.
Blend, then add corn.
Deep fry by teaspoonfuls.

title: eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant.
Cut into small pieces and boil until tender. Then mash.
Add eggs, onion, flour, salt and pepper.
Make into patties and fry.

title: baked whole ham
directions: Place in a roasting pan.
Cover with foil; seal as tight as possible.
Place in a 225° oven.
Bake 7 to 8 hours.
When cool enough, slice as is or remove as much fat as possible and then slice.

title: russian mints
directions: Place liners in muffin tins.
Place
vanilla
wafers in each tin.
Cream butter and sugar; blend
in melted chocolate. Add eggs
one at a time and beat well.
Add
flavoring.
Fill each tin 3/4 full.
Add a dollop of Cool Whip, a sprinkling of chopped pecans and half a maraschino cherry.
Freeze in muffin tins.
When firm and solid frozen, remove and
store in Ziploc bags.
Serve frozen, unthawed.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Saute onions in oil until transparent.
Add beans, pimiento, mushroom soup and milk.
Fry together, stirring lightly until thoroughly heated.

title: mexican roasted corn
directions: Remove husks and silk from corn.
Combine chopped green chiles and remaining ingredients in a small bowl, stir well. Brush green chile mixture evenly over corn.
Wrap each ear in heavy-duty aluminum foil to seal.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Turn after 15 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: italian chicken dinner
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients over medium heat.
Add pepper to taste and tomato sauce.
Place chicken in 2-quart casserole dish, sprayed with Pam.
Pour mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add cheese.
Put in oven to melt.
Serve over noodles.

title: caramel layer chocolate bars
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk in saucepan on stove. Set aside.
Combine dry cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Mix by hand.
Press half the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread caramel mixture over the chips.
Crumble the remaining cake mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Cool.

title: banana shake
directions: Blend in blender.
Each serving contains 65 calories.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground chuck; add onion, garlic, pimento, green pepper, mushrooms, tomato sauce, water, chili powder and red pepper or hot pepper sauce.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Make a paste of the flour and water.
Stir into meat mixture.
Add ripe olives.
Cook over low heat until it comes to a boil.
Season to taste.
Layer mixture, grated cheese and crushed chips into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes until hot clear through.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until tender. When vegetables are tender, add bacon fryings and salt and pepper.
Mix together milk, sugar and cornstarch.
Add to cabbage, stirring constantly. Reduce heat, let stand, and ready to serve!
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, vinegar and sugar.
Clean broccoli and drain; add Mozzarella cheese and onion.
Add mayo mixture and combine well. Chill.
Add bacon just before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Add macaroni to 2 quarts of boiling salted water and cook for 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Drain cooked macaroni.
Put in a bowl.
Stir in 1 tablespoon butter and egg.
Add 2 1/2 cups of grated cheese.
In bowl combine mustard, salt, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Pour milk mixture over top of macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese and paprika on top. Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: big and easy pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits, then separate each biscuit into 2 layers.
Arrange on an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press biscuits to form crust.
Spread tomato sauce over dough; sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Stir salad dressing mix into ground beef along with onion and pepper; spoon over cheese.
Top with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until crust is golden brown.
Can be made ahead, covered and refrigerated up to 2 hours.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop popcorn.
Mix popcorn, M&M's and nuts in large bowl.
Melt oleo.
Add oil and marshmallows.
Stir over low heat until melted. Stir and cook constantly for 1 minute.
Pour in bowl over popcorn.
Mix.
Press into pans.
This will make any size cake you wish.
It works well in loaf pans also.

title: sweet potato waffles
directions: Blend together the sweet potatoes, milk, egg whites and oil. Add flour and baking powder; mix until smooth.
Preheat waffle iron.
Coat the grids with nonstick spray.
Add 3/4 cup of the batter.
Cook for approximately 8 minutes, or until they are cooked through.
Repeat to make 3 more waffles.

title: caramel graham cracker cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line large rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Place graham crackers flat on prepared pan.
In small saucepan over moderate heat, melt butter and brown sugar; bring to boil.
Stir constantly while boiling 5 minutes.
Pour caramelized mixture evenly over graham crackers.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake in oven 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut between each square.
Cool completely.
(I break crackers in hand.)

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O; stir into cranberry sauce and pineapple. Stir with a fork.
Add walnuts.
Chill until partly set, then pour half of mixture in Bundt pan and chill until firm.
Let remaining half stand at room temperature.
When first half is firm, spread sour cream evenly over the gelatin in mold.
Gently spoon remainder of the mixture over top of sour cream.
Chill overnight. Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut candy
directions: Put sugar into saucepan and stir until sugar melts.
It will be caramel color.
Immediately stir in peanuts.
Pour on oiled surface.
It will harden quickly.
Cut or break into pieces.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Dissolve in 1/2 cup sour cream.
Mix well and bake until done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Beat eggs well until fluffy. Add Bisquick, onion powder and Parmesan to form a pasty consistency. Add zucchini; mix well. Add salt and pepper to taste. Place mixture into a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut in half lengthwise (while still hot) and scoop out centers, being careful not to puncture skin of the potato.
Put hot potato in mixing bowl and beat with electric beater while adding butter and cream.
After mixture is smooth, add sour cream, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Add cheese and mix again.
Put spoonfuls of mixture into potato shells.
Top with shredded cheese and chives.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes, or until cheese melts and mixture is bubbly.
This recipe can be made a day ahead.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cherry bonbons
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light. Stir in flour and nuts until well blended.
Cover and chill 30 minutes or until firm enough to handle.
On lightly floured surface, shape in 1-inch thick slices.
Turn cut side up; place cherry in center of each slice.
With lightly floured hands, shape in balls, covering cherry completely with dough.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet; chill 15 minutes.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove to racks to cool.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Separate cabbage leaves and immerse in boiling water for about 1 minute, until softened.
Beat egg.
Add ground beef, onion, rice, milk, salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon goulash mix.
Combine with fork.
Blend remaining goulash mix, tomatoes and tomato sauce in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Place about 1 teaspoon meat mixture on cabbage leaf. Roll up securely; place in large, buttered shallow baking dish. Pour tomato mixture over rolls.
Cover; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt in one large bowl.
Mix oleo, cocoa and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla. Mix well and pour into greased cookie sheet pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hamburger helper
directions: Brown hamburger in 10-inch skillet; drain off grease.
Add 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Bring back to a boil and cook macaroni until tender.
When macaroni is done, add cream soup.
Stir until blended.
Now, add cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.

title: almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with sugar, soda and salt. Mix in shortening and knead with both hands for 8 to 10 minutes. Combine egg and almond extract.
Stir into flour mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on baking sheets and make depression on top with the thumb.
Dip blunt end of chopstick in red food coloring and press into top of each cookie.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce and sugar together.
Pour over frozen or thawed wings.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until done.
Uncover pan and broil for about 5 minutes until chicken is a little brown.

title: ultimate chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease large shallow baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of the rice on bottom.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; place over rice.
Mix together soups, butter or margarine, milk and sherry.
Pour 1/2 over chicken; sprinkle remainder of rice over chicken, followed by remainder of soup mixture.
Sprinkle top with cheese and almonds.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: brownies
directions: Place in bowl in order given.
Mix on medium speed of mixer for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan. Frost with Satin Frosting.

title: the president's choice
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces; dip in flour and brown in hot fat in skillet.
When chicken pieces are browned, remove to casserole.
Add chopped onion to fat and brown lightly; add remaining ingredients to fat and onion in skillet and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour sauce over browned chicken in casserole; cover casserole with aluminum foil and bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 1 hour.
Serve piping hot with hot rolls and potato salad and sliced tomatoes, if you like.
It's delicious.

title: yummy fudge bars
directions: Mix oats, flour, sugar, pecans, salt, soda and butter together until crumbly.
Press into large cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
In saucepan, heat oil and chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in condensed milk and mix well.
Spread over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(You can reserve some of the crumbly mixture to top chocolate.)
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Make into balls.
Make syrup with remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: shrimp soft fried noodles(mi xao)
directions: Rice is very important in Vietnam meals; without rice it would not be a complete Vietnam dinner.
These are mainly two kinds of rice:

title: secret code buns
directions: Thaw dough.
Sprinkle flour on counter and put dough and raisins on top of it.
Work as many raisins as you can into the dough; work with your hand 2 to 3 minutes.
Cover dough with plastic wrap.
Let rest 20 minutes.
Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and stir until mixed.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over mixture.
Put 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar in large plastic bag. Cut dough in 30 small balls.
Shake 3 at a time in bag and put into prepared pan.
Rise until doubled or 1 hour.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Cool in the pan 10 minutes.
Put cookie sheet on top and flip pan over.
Eat while warm.

title: cheesy broccoli bread
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Beat all ingredients together with a spoon.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into one cup of hot oil in heavy frying pan and cook slowly on medium heat, turning often.

title: campfire casserole
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp, remove bacon and drain on paper towel reserving 2 Tbsp. drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute potatoes, onion, 1/2 tsp. salt, and 1/4 tsp. pepper in hot drippings, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes or until browned.
Whisk together eggs, remaining 1/2 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper.
Pour over potatoes in skillet. Cook over medium heat 4 minutes or until eggs are set, stirring if necessary.
Sprinkle with bacon and if desired cheese.
Serve with salsa or ketchup.

title: so good snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together Smart Beat, powdered sugar, vanilla, almond extract and Egg Beaters until smooth.
Add flour and blend thoroughly.
Chill dough 1 hour.
On a small plate, mix together the granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Drop dough by spoonful into the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
The dough will be very sticky. Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture over dough until it is coated enough.
Next, place the coated balls on a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields about 5 dozen cookies.

title: creamy chef's dressing(low-calorie)
directions: Process all ingredients until smooth in a blender or the work bowl of a food processor fitted with a metal blade.
Process until smooth.
Keep covered and refrigerated.
Makes 1 cup.
Serves 16; 1 tablespoon per serving.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Add soda to buttermilk, then add sugar and corn syrup.
Boil until mixture reaches candy stage.
Add butter and nuts.
Pour into greased pan or onto a cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: corn and cheese chowder
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Stir in corn, milk, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Add cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle parsley over chowder.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Layer the ingredients in a 9 x 13 dish. Serve with Tostitos or corn chips. Can be made the night before (leave tomatoes off until just before serving).

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bake at 325° in 2 round cake pans until done.

title: pear torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; beat in vanilla.
Add flour and mix well until blended.
Spread in bottom and up 1 1/2-inches on sides of greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Spread Cream Cheese Filling evenly over crust.
Arrange pears decoratively over filling.
Sprinkle nut topping over pears.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until brown.
Serve cool or warm.

title: penache icing
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt butter and add brown sugar. Add milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm consistency.

title: sauerkraut(can)
directions: Using 1 gallon shredded turnip, add 1 tablespoon salt.
Fill glass jar to 1/2-inch from brim with turnips, salt and water. Screw top on, then make a slight turn back.
Mixture will start fermenting in 3 or 4 days.
Keep in cool place about 6 weeks.

title: cool carrots
directions: Cook carrots about 10 minutes.
They should be crunchy.
Mix oil, sugar and vinegar.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over carrots.
Marinate several days if possible.
Good side dish.

title: pulled mints
directions: Bring water to a boil on high and add sugar and cream of tartar; stir until it dissolves, then cover and cook for 3 minutes.
Uncover and, without stirring, cook on high until it reaches a syrupy stage (262° on candy thermometer).
Do not touch the thermometer to the bottom of the pan.
Pour into little puddles on a greased pan; let cool.
Pull until desired size.
Cut with clean scissors.
Roll in powdered sugar until coated.

title: caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, stir crust mixes, sugar, butter and water with fork until crumbs are well moistened.
Press crumbs firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Stir first 2 ingredients together with fork. Mix together. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add drained can of peas, mushroom soup and drained tuna.
Mix all together and put into baking dish. Lay cheese across top to cover.
Crumble chips and add to top of cheese.
Bake in oven at 250° for 1 hour or until chips start to brown slightly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn oysters
directions: Combine corn, egg and flour/seasoning.
To each tablespoon of this mixture, add one oyster.
Drop in deep fat or cook on a hot, well-greased grill.
Serves 4.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, salt and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll in small balls and flatten with small glass (flat bottom dipped in sugar).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: banana muffins
directions: Put egg in cup; fill with milk.
Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add water and mix well. Add vanilla; mix.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine the 6 ingredients; beat for 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn out on a wire rack to cool.
Frost with frosting.

title: red-green salad
directions: Use 15 x 10 x 2-inch tin or smaller but deeper pan.
Set lime jello in pan until firm.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Sprinkle chips and nuts in bottom of crusts.
Mix well 1 stick melted butter, 1 cup corn syrup, 1 cup sugar and 4 eggs.
Pour into crusts and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quail and gravy
directions: Marinate birds overnight in Zesty Italian dressing.
Bread and fry in Puritan oil until golden brown.
Saturate onions in oil; add Lipton onion soup.
Put in 3/4 cup flour; stir 1 quart hot water in.
Stir constantly to make gravy smooth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Good with grits, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Mix as you would a regular pound cake.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use your favorite white icing.
Very pretty and delicious for Christmas, Valentine's Day or Fourth of July.

title: sweet apple dumpling
directions: For crust, use first 6 ingredients.
Sift flour; cut in shortening, beaten egg and water.
Add vinegar; stir into flour. Mix and chill.
Pare and core apples.
Combine and blend all other ingredients.
Fill the core hollows with fruit mixture and spread remainder over the fruit.
Roll out dough between sheets of floured waxed paper until it is about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut it into 8 squares.
Brush the squares with white of an egg.
Place an apple in each square.
Press edges together using a little water, if necessary to make them stick.
Prick the tops.

title: cranberry dream salad
directions: In blender, whip the cream.
Remove to large mixing bowl.
Add well drained pineapple.
Put cranberry sauce in blender; cover and liquify until smooth.
Add mayonnaise, sugar and cream cheese and process until well blended.
Add nuts and process only until chopped.
Fold into whipped cream and pineapple.
Pour into mold or tray and freeze.
To serve, let stand at room temperature 15 minutes.
Turn out on lettuce and slice.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix the drained fruit cocktail with the cake mix. Add the eggs and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured round or rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and firm in center.

title: nanny's pork chop spaghetti
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add enough water to cover pork chops and onions. Cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain spaghetti.
Pour pork chop-onion mixture over spaghetti.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: green party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water in punch bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour in pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Stir.
Add sherbet.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs well; mix with other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk and powdered sugar to make a dipping texture.
Add chocolate chips.
Serve with graham cracker sticks.

title: orange balls
directions: Chop wafers fine in blender.
Mix well with remaining ingredients.
Roll into one-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados with fork and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana split refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water, set aside at room temperature.
Prepare and bake cake as directed on package.
Cool cake 20 minutes, poke holes in cake with a knife. With cup slowly pour mixture of gelatin over cake.
Set in refrigerator while preparing topping.
Blend topping mix, instant pudding, cold milk and vanilla.
Beat until stiff, spread on cake. Store cake in refrigerator and serve chilled.
Serves 6.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Add milk to beaten eggs.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Cut in squares.
Serves 8.

title: seafood and rice casserole
directions: Add salad dressing to rice while hot.
Combine with other ingredients and place in casserole. Top with slivered almonds. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
This can be made ahead and frozen, but allow to come to room temperature before baking.

title: pizza
directions: brown meat. Drain. Put biscuits on pizza pan and mash together to cover pan. Top with remaining ingredients except pepperoni. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes. If adding pepperoni, add last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: best black beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Discard water.
Add water to cover plus 1/2 inch.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours on stove.

title: bacon & egg casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender not brown. Stir in flour. Add milk all at once. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add cheese, stir until melted. Place 1/2 eggs on bottom of baking dish. Pour 1/2 cheese sauce over eggs. Sprinkle 1/2 chips and 1/2 bacon. Repeat layers. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: earthquakes - lemon cookies
directions: Roll into teaspoon size balls. Roll cookie balls in granulated sugar. Cookies will be sticky. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cookies will flatten and crackle as they bake.

title: spanish rice
directions: Using 2 tablespoons butter, saute the onion, garlic and green chili
or
green bell pepper until tender.	In separate pan add remaining butter and rice and lightly brown rice.
Set aside. Heat
to
boiling the tomato sauce, bay leaf, salt and chicken stock.
Add
the
sauteed
vegetables
to the boiling liquid and then
add the rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until rice is tender and not moist.

title: little pizzas
directions: Fry the ground beef and sausage; drain grease. Add the pizza sauce. Add the Velveeta cheese to all ingredients in skillet. Stir until cheese is melted. Spoon on party rye bread.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, eggs, and vanilla.
Mix together flour and oatmeal.
Put small amounts in blender until all is powdered.
Add salt, baking powder, and baking soda.
Mix together with creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips, grated chocolate, nuts, and mix well.
Make golf ball size cookies.
Place on ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes. Yield:
112 cookies.

title: benja's potato casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
(except	corn
flakes) together. Bake at 350°
until bubbly hot.	Remove from oven and add corn flakes. Drizzle melted butter over top.
Cook about 5 minutes.

title: ground beef snack quiches
directions: In a saucepan, over medium heat, cook beef, garlic powder, and pepper until meat is no longer pink; drain and set aside.
In a bowl, combine the biscuit mix and cornmeal; cut in butter.
Add enough water to form a soft dough.
Press onto the bottom and up the sides of greased miniature muffin cups.
Place teaspoonfuls of beef mixture into each shell.
In a bowl, combine the egg, cream, onion, red pepper, salt and cayenne.
Pour into beef mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: best chilled beets
directions: Drain the beets, reserving 1 1/2 cups of juice in a large saucepan.
Add cornstarch to juice and mix well.
Add beets and remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until the sauce is slightly thickened, stirring often.
Remove spice bag.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: beans plus
directions: Mix all together and heat in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 or more.

title: overnight salad
directions: Place shredded cabbage and cut up green pepper mixture in a bowl in layers, alternating with sliced onion rings.
Top each layer with sugar.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In medium bowl, mix together oats, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon. Stir in melted butter and water to form a crumbly mixture. In a large saucepan, mix together cranberry sauce and cornstarch. Bring to boil and remove from heat. Stir in apples. Spread into 8 x 8
glass baking dish. Crumble oat mixture over apples. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm.

title: genevieve's hot milk sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl add ingredients in the order listed.
Be sure to mix continually with a mixer and then quickly place in ungreased oblong pan and bake for 45 minutes. The bubbles in the batter are important to make a spongy cake.
Ice with Caramel Coconut Frosting if desired.

title: lemon angel pie
directions: Make meringue by beating egg whites until they make stiff peaks.
Beat in sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat until it forms stiff shiny peaks.
Put meringue in a greased 9 inch pie plate. Bake 20 minutes at 250° and then an additional 40 minutes at 275°. Cool meringue crust.
It will fall.
Mix lemon pie filling as per package directions and allow to cool.
Whip the cream (do not sweeten) or the Dream Whip according to package directions. Place 1/2 of cream on top of crust.
Spread on filling.
Cover with remaining cream and make peaks.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: scot munro's vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well; mix in sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir in the cream and mix well.
Pour into the freezer can and fill to 2/3 full with half and half.
Freeze as the freezer instruction indicates.
Makes 4 quarts (1 gallon).

title: pecan patties(non-dairy)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon into very small amount of cooking oil (medium temperature).
Brown patties on both sides.
Makes about 18 patties.

title: skillet vegetable side dish
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Cook and stir carrots, onion, cabbage and green pepper for 5 minutes.
