Add remaining ingredients; cook and stir 5 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add rhubarb and stir until rhubarb is coated.
Put into a greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and sprinkle mixture over the rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: stuffed shells florentine
directions: Cook shells; when done, drain portion of water allowing shells to remain in warm water.
Mix Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and spinach.
Remove one shell at a time.
Stuff each shell with mixture.
Pour 1/2 of spaghetti sauce into bottom of a large shallow casserole.
Arrange stuffed shells in casserole.
Pour remaining sauce over shells. Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 8.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.

Beat eggs and set 2 Tbsp. aside. Mix all other ingredients. Line bottom of baking pan with 1 can of the crescent rolls (rolled out). Pour ingredients on top and then roll out the other can of rolls and place on top of the mixture.
Brush with the remaining egg mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish with Pam.
Line bottom with triangles of dough.
Save 3 triangles for top.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add zucchini, onion and spices.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Combine beaten eggs and Mozzarella cheese and stir into zucchini mixture.
Pour mixture into pastry lined dish.
Place reserved triangles of dough on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°, covered with foil.
Uncover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Put pepper, celery and onion in a little water and cook until soft; then drain off water.
Add to beans.
Add 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt, 1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup catsup.
Put in baking dish and top with catsup and strips of bacon.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: captain's casserole
directions: Heat soup, milk and cheese until cheese is melted.
Combine rice and pepper in greased shallow pan.
Drain tomatoes, measuring 1/2 cup juice, stirring juice and water into rice.
Slice tomatoes; arrange most of tomatoes on rice.
Add onion, tuna and olives.
Pour on sauce.
Sprinkle on chips or crumbs; add remaining tomatoes.
Add Parmesan or Mozzarella cheese and oregano.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter shallow 2-quart baking dish. Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Turn into dish. Sprinkle crackers and almonds evenly over top.
Bake until heated through, about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: meatless mexican lasagna
directions: Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray. Mix together Ricotta cheese, cottage cheese and chilies; set aside. Cook lasagna noodles; rinse under cold water. Drain and cut to fit pan. Mix pinto beans with spaghetti sauce. Spread a little sauce on bottom of pan. Place half the noodles, half the cheese mixture, half the sauce and bean mixture and half the Monterey Jack cheese. Repeat layers. Cook at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on thickness. Crock-pot can be used on low setting for 6 to 8 hours.

title: potato lasagna
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Boil potatoes in salted water until done.
Saute onion in oleo until transparent.
Drain potatoes and mash, adding 1/2 onion mixture and the grated cheese.
Layer noodles in well buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add 1/2 potato mixture, another layer of noodles, remaining 1/2 potato mixture, ending with another layer of noodles on top.
Drizzle remaining onion mixture over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: potato casserole(makes 8 servings)
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Beat until light and fluffy. Beat in the butter and cream cheese, then beat in the sour cream, nutmeg, pepper and salt.

title: pies
directions: For chocolate pies, add 2 tablespoons cocoa.
For coconut pies, add 1 cup coconut.

title: gooey butter cake with coconut
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and put in bottom of pan. Next mix the last 5 ingredients together and put on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's cocoa pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; put into your saucepan that has the egg yolks and milk, stirring well while cooking, until thick and then add vanilla.
Makes enough for 1 pie.
Can use the egg whites for meringue if want or use whipped cream.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash all ingredients with potato masher.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: flatbread
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add milk and roll very thin.
Heat griddle and oven to 300° and bake one side on griddle. Put on baking dish and bake in oven until crisp.

title: chicken and yellow rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, water and soup in greased casserole dish.
Place chicken breasts on top of mixture.
Cover and bake for approximately 35 minutes.
Uncover and top with onion rings.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes, until bubbly.

title: plain pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt together 3 times; cut in Crisco and add water, a little at a time, until mixture will hold together.
Roll on floured board to desired size.
Makes 2 pastry shells.
Bake according to filling recipe.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Place wafers in pie pan.
Stir Eagle Brand milk and frozen lemonade together until creamy.
Add whipped cream and pour over wafers.
Cool and serve with lemon peel if desired.
This is real lemony.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding using 3 cups milk.
Lay down one layer of graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pudding over crackers. Make another layer of crackers.
Pour remainder of pudding over crackers.
Make one more layer of crackers.
Mix cocoa, sugar, evaporated milk and butter in saucepan.
Heat until bubbly.
Add vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour over cracker layer.
Refrigerate and serve with a
dab of whipped topping.

title: blueberry angel dessert
directions: In a large bowl beat cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip an cake cubes.
Spread evenly into an ungreased 9x13 inch dish.
Top with pie filling and refrigerate at least 2 hours before cutting.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Place butter in pan and brown onion.
Brown sausage.
Drain fat from sausage.
Put all in a large skillet with lid.
Place uncooked cabbage and noodles in skillet.
Add several cups of water.
Bring to a boil and add bouillon cube, more cubes if desired.
Stir occasionally, until noodles are cooked.

title: italian pasta bake
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain.
Stir in spaghetti, sauce and 1/2 cup of the parmesan cheese.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Top with mozzarella cheese and remaining 1/4 cup parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chili
directions: Put pinto beans on and bring to a boil.
Turn off and let sit for 1 hour.
Drain water off; put fresh water on beans and cook until done.
Drain beans and save water.
Fry sausage, onion, garlic and jalapeno until well done and brown.
Drain sausage mixture.
Then add sausage and pinto beans; measure water from beans if needed.
Add enough water to
make 5 cups liquid.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder and
Kitchen Bouquet and put in crock-pot; simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix together and place in a dish greased with mayonnaise. Refrigerate.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine Bisquick, sugar, soda and corn meal.
Blend in butter, eggs and milk.
Bake in a large (10 x 15-inch) ungreased glass baking dish at 325° for 40 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Moist, buttery and delicious.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Grill pork chops on outside grill.
Once completely cooked, sprinkle on fresh oregano.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in 4 pieces each.
Place sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Add biscuit pieces a few at a time and shake to coat.
Then place pieces in a greased tube pan.
Layer in pieces, putting pecans onto top of each layer until all pieces are in pan. Bring brown sugar and margarine to a boil in saucepan.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Allow to cool 15 minutes before turning out of pan onto serving dish.
Turn top side up to serve.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together lightly chicken or turkey, celery, almonds, green pepper, pimento, onion, salt, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Put alternate layers of salad mixture and crushed potato chips in buttered pans (2 pans), size 14 x 9 x 2-inch.
Top with layer of grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese stuffed peppers
directions: Remove seeds from peppers; boil 5 minutes and drain upside down.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Combine all ingredients except 1 cup cheese.
Fill peppers with mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in greased baking dish at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Put 1/2 c. butter in baking pan.
Mix ingredients.
Pour into the buttered pan.
Bake at 275° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry lemon parfait
directions: Whip cream to form stiff peaks. In another bowl mix 1/4 cream into curd and blend; then fold rest of cream and lemon peel. Chill.

title: potato salad(serves 100 people)
directions: Boil cubed potatoes until tender and drain; add butter. Add relish,
eggs,
pimentos, onions, mustard and mayonnaise. Mix well.
Add	red
pepper, salt
and	black pepper to taste. Sprinkle top
with	paprika
for
color.
This
will serve 100 people. (You
may
always figure 2 1/2 servings for each pound of potatoes).

title: cathie's favorite snack
directions: Slice banana; sprinkle with chips.
Microwave for 25 seconds. Eat while still warm alone or with ice cream.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pare eggplant, if desired.
Cut in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Dip each slice, first into eggs, then into crumbs.
Saute in hot oil until golden brown on both sides.
Place layer of eggplant in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with some Parmesan cheese, oregano and Mozzarella cheese.
Then cover well with some tomato sauce.
Repeat until all eggplant is used, topping last layer of sauce with several slices of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour or until sauce is bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: praline cake squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in peaches and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Cook ground meat, zucchini, onion and peppers in a large skillet until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, picante sauce, pinto beans, bouillon granules, cumin, salt and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Lightly spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick Pam spray.
Arrange as follows:
1/3 meat sauce, 3 lasagne noodles, 1/2 cheese, 1/3 meat, all sour cream, remaining noodles and remaining meat sauce.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and olives. Return to oven until cheese melts.
Yields 8 servings.

title: orange cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Add flour, sifted with
baking
powder,
alternately
with
milk to creamed mixture;
add orange
extract.
Pour
into two greased and floured 8-inch square pans and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: 5 minute brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Melt shortening.
Add cocoa; stir.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in vanilla, flour and salt.
Fold in nuts. Spread in pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kolachy
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little of the cold water.
Combine shortening, oleo, egg yolks, yeast and water.
Add flour and salt. Knead dough.
Leave in refrigerator overnight (this dough will be sticky).
Add some sugar to nuts to desired sweetness.
Add a little canned milk and egg white to moisten.

title: gyoza (pot stickers)
directions: Combine sausage, garlic, bok choy, and onion.
Mix well.
Coat one side of wonton wrapper with egg.
Put 1 teaspoon sausage mixture on egg side of wrapper.
Fold wrapper in half.
Crimp edges.
Brown on medium low heat in a small amount of sesame oil. When both sides are crispy brown, add a small amount of water to pan and cover for one minute.
Serve with hot mustard.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add cream cheese, 2 1/2 tablespoons sugar, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread over cool crust. Top with 1 can blueberry pie filling and refrigerate.

title: old-fashioned brown sugar syrup
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan and bring to boil.
Cover and boil gently 10 minutes.
Add maple flavoring.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and bananas, beating until light. Alternately add flour mix and milk; beat after each addition until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until tests done.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and salt, then stir in milk.
When thick, add cheese, stirring until melted.
Grease casserole dish. Put in half of the asparagus, half of the eggs and half of the cheese sauce.
Repeat.
Put bread crumbs on the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Let cool.
Combine egg, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients (flour, cocoa, salt and sugar) alternately with soda mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle top with brown sugar, chocolate chips and walnuts. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip on a 12-inch serving plate.
In a small bowl, mash the avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Spread over bean dip.

title: fried cottage cheese
directions: In skillet, melt cottage cheese with butter (scouts don't count calories).
Add parsley flakes and black pepper.
Serve over kloski noodles for a delightfully mild cheese sauce.
Another culinary legend from the days when Pastor Larson was chief cook at Camp Cayuga.

title: bat wings(meat for halloween)
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken wings.
Dip in melted butter.
Coat with instant potato flakes.
Salt and pepper chicken wings.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste with coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Add salt and buttermilk with flour and vanilla.
Add soda and vinegar.
Do not beat hard.
Just blend. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cook in 4 (9-inch) pans.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Cut up chicken in small pieces and cook with rotel in medium skillet until sauce is almost cooked off.
In
another skillet, spray with Pam.
Stove should be on about medium heat.

Place tortilla in skillet, Place about 2-3 tbsp of chicken mix on 1/2 of tortilla, sprinkle with cheese then fold tortilla over then turn over and heat on the other side just enough for the cheese to melt.

title: tuna casserole for two
directions: Use small casserole.
Crumble a layer of tuna fish.
Crumble a layer of potato chips; repeat with another layer of each.
Pour soup over top and bake in moderate oven to heat through.
Serve hot.
Makes two servings.

title: diane's mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix together.
Divide filling among tortillas.
Spread and roll like jelly roll.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Twist ends to seal. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut in 1/2 to 1-inch slices.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: saffron rice salad
directions: *May substitute ground turmeric for the saffron, if desired.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix into balls and place in large frying pan.
Cover with a can of tomato soup mixed with water.
Cover pan and cook on low for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chuck wagon hamburgers
directions: Crumble bread in bowl.
Add water and egg and mix until bread is moist.
Add hamburger, onion, salt and pepper to taste and a dash of garlic salt.
Mix and shape into patties.
Put on wax paper.
Stack and store until ready to cook.

title: orange delight
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 1/2 cup of juice.
Mix orange Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup pineapple juice; set aside. Mix pudding with 1 cup milk.
Combine Jell-O and pudding together. Fold in Cool Whip.
Add pineapple.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Garnish with mandarin oranges.

title: pecan roll
directions: Bring sugar, cream and syrup to soft ball over slow fire or in double boiler.
Add dates and return to fire, stirring constantly, until dates are dissolved.
Remove from fire and add nuts and vanilla.
Form in rolls any size desired.
Place in refrigerator until hard.
Then roll in finely chopped nuts or powdered sugar. Slice and serve.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: crispy fried mushrooms
directions: Mix flour, salt, mustard, paprika, basil and pepper in large plastic food storage bag; set aside.
Place buttermilk in small bowl.
Dip a few mushrooms at a time in buttermilk.
Place in bag with flour mix.
Shake to coat, heat 2 to 3 inches of oil in deep fryer or heavy pan to 375°.
Fry a few mushrooms at a time, 2 to 3 minutes or until deep golden brown, turning over several times. Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with mustard sauce or catsup, if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: creole limas
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove and brown onions.
Add bacon, onion and remaining ingredients to drained limas.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Sift sugar.
Mix sugar, chips, salt and butter over medium heat, until it begins to boil and all chips are melted.
Stir vigorously for 1 more minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Let cool.

title: filled ring mold salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges, reserving juices.
Add enough water to reserved juices to measure 3 cups.
Soften unflavored gelatin in 1 1/4 cup juice mixture for 1 minute.
Bring remaining juice mixture to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in softened gelatin and orange gelatin until dissolved.
Pour over sherbet in large bowl; mix well.
Cool slightly.
Spoon into 6-cup ring mold sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Chill overnight.
Combine mandarin oranges, pineapple, coconut flakes and sour cream in bowl; mix well.
Chill overnight.
Unmold ring onto serving plate lined with leaf lettuce.
Stir marshmallows into fruit mixture. Spoon into center of mold.

title: onion-cucumber salad
directions: Thinly slice the onion and cucumbers.
Separate the onion into rings.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over the onion and cucumbers.
Marinate about an hour.

title: easy cheesy crescent
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine the first 4 ingredients. Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Press 2 rectangles over bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Spread half of cheese mixture over dough.
Place remaining rectangles over cheese, gently stretching to cover.
Spread with remaining cheese mixture; sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and dice into 1-inch cubes.
Cook in salt water until very tender.
Brown onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in slow oven about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients except for soup mixture, cheese and potato chips
, then pour soup mixture over all.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Boil chicken in water (can use for soup at later date if you wish).
When done, cut chicken off bones into large chunks.
Cook broccoli.
Put bed of rice in casserole dish.
Cover with chicken pieces (as much as you want).
Cover chicken with broccoli.
Mix soup with 3/4 can of milk.
Pour over broccoli.
Cover with foil. Set oven at 325°; cook about 30 minutes.

title: shrimp-vegetable salad
directions: Mix ingredients in salad bowl.

title: poultry glaze
directions: Mix together and cook on low until thick.
Put on poultry the last 30 minutes of cooking.

title: easy spaghetti
directions: Bring water to boil and add soup mix.
Add spaghetti and cook until tender.
Do not drain.
Brown ground beef; pour off grease. Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, oregano, parsley and garlic.
Mix well and simmer for a couple of minutes.
Mix with spaghetti mixture.
It will be soupy, but will thicken as it sits.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix all ingredients and pour in small pan (sprayed with cooking spray).

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop green onions and meat fine.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Save enough meat to sprinkle over top of cheese ball after formed.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Put these two mixtures together.
Mix well. Put rhubarb into unbaked pie crust.
Pour mixture over rhubarb and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Thaw spinach.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Add milk, margarine, onion, eggs and cheeses.
Squeeze out water from spinach; add to mixture.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake approximately 25 to 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Cool approximately 20 minutes and cut into squares.

title: matt's favorite birthday treat
directions: Melt marshmallows with margarine in saucepan over low heat. Stir occasionally until smooth.
Blend in peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
Press lightly into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: fried pecans
directions: Preparation:
Measure and have all ingredients ready.
Pour oil in skillet; set aside.
Spread clean cloth on countertop for draining.
Have salt shaker nearby.
Set up colander in sink.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour.
Then add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Break pieces of dough off; roll in flour and pat onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine the milk and eggs.
Mix well with other ingredients and pour into oblong glass baking dish.
Bake slowly for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until done.
Stir from bottom 3 times while baking.
It may be the intermittent stirring that produces the luscious custard consistency.

title: chinese noodle tuna salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, breaking the tuna into fine pieces.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Just before serving, add peas and noodles.
Stir and serve.
Can add more ingredients for larger crowd.

title: southern fried ham with red eye gravy
directions: Place lard and ham in cold iron skillet; cover and cook slowly over medium heat for 20 minutes, turning frequently.
Remove lid. Cook 5 minutes longer.
Remove ham; drain.
Add to drippings 1 cup cold water.
Bring to a boil; pour over ham.
Serve immediately with hot, homemade biscuits.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy potato oven omelet
directions: In a large bowl, combine 3/4 cup onions with remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 8-inch square glass dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining onions.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients like pie dough until crumbly.
Take 1/2 cup crumbs and set aside.
Add buttermilk with soda added to it.
Mix for a short time; batter will be lumpy.
Pour into an ungreased 8-inch square dish.
Pour 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients very well. Shape into bars. Put on a large cookie sheet that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes. Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: fondue burgers
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add liquid slowly and stir. Add cheese.
Cook over low flame until thick.
Serve over hamburger, bun and all.

title: quick cobbler(quick and easy)
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish. Mix the next 6 ingredients together. Pour into casserole with the melted oleo. Pour fruit over the batter. Do not stir. If you use unsweetened fruit, add 1/4 cup sugar more. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey custard(low calorie)
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg until foamy.
Add cornstarch and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add honey and vanilla; mix well. Slowly beat in hot milk.
Place 5 paper-lined 2 1/2-inch foil muffin cups in baking dish.
Pour in custard.
Pour hot water into dish to reach halfway up sides of cups.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Chill and serve.
Makes 5 servings, 53 calories per serving.

title: yorkie
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Add milk gradually while beating with rotary beater, then beat in eggs.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: straw-ba-nut ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed until frothy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Stir in condensed milk and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine fruit and nuts and fold in whipped topping. Add fruit mixture to egg mixture and stir.
Pour into a gallon freezer container and add enough milk to fill can 3/4 full. Freeze and serve.

title: potato and beef bake
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
When done, mash.
Brown ground beef, onions and green peppers.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan, starting with potatoes first.
Then add a layer of meat, then cheese, until all is gone.
Good to have cheese as last layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and mix in sugar, flour, milk and corn syrup.
Blend in eggs and vanilla. Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin and beat well, then add to dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and nuts; stir well.
Bake 70 to 80 minutes at 325° in well-greased, floured loaf pan.

title: squash pies
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 2 uncooked pie shells until firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add chopped nuts and salt.
Blend all together.
Bake in a Bundt pan or fluted pan approximately 1 hour.
Test with a toothpick for doneness.
May ice with vanilla or cream cheese frosting.

title: ina's cranberry jelly salad
directions: Spread cranberry sauce in the bottom of an ice tray or small shallow dish.
Whip the cream until stiff and fold in pecans and mayonnaise.
Spread this mixture over the cranberry sauce. Freeze. Once the salad has frozen, cover with plastic wrap to keep ice crystals from forming.
Cut into squares for serving.
Serves 4.

title: chili
directions: Mix meat, beer, tomato sauce and salt.
Cook 40 minutes, then mash with potato masher.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes longer.
(You can cook all day and night in a slow cooker.)

title: biscuits
directions: Mix well and drop onto floured board and pat into shape. Place in greased pan and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry-rice salad
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions.
Add rice and mix well.
Chill until set.
Stir congealed gelatin with fork until broken up.
Add pineapple, marshmallows, coconut and whipped topping.
Mix well.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 10 servings.

title: a good dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, dressing and chipped beef that has been chopped or broken into small pieces.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: grandmother mims' pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with spoon.
Add flour, sugar, syrup, salt and vanilla.
Beat lightly.
Melt butter and pour into batter.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into prepared pie crust.

title: alison's award winning chili
directions: Cut up salt pork and brown in oil in a large skillet.
When pork is about half cooked, add onions.
When salt pork is completely cooked, put in the rest of the ingredients, except spices, and mix well.
Add spices (they weren't measured as they went in, but I'd guess that this is in the multiple tablespoon range) and cook on low for an hour or two.

title: ham and cheese souffle
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of bread on bottom. Cover with 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of ham.
Add another layer of each.
Mix eggs, milk and salt and pour over all.
Melt butter and pour on top.
Refrigerate 6 hours or so or overnight.
Bake about 1 hour at 400° in pan of hot water.
Cover with foil if it gets too brown.
Warms up nice if leftover.
I'm lazy, I don't cube the bread!

title: raisin pineapple muffins
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, juice and orange peel.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir into juice mixture until moistened.
Spoon batter into six muffin cups coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 large muffins.
Preparation: 20 minutes.
Bake: 25 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix spinach, cream cheese and Swiss cheese together in microwave-safe bowl.
Add a small amount of garlic salt.
Heat in microwave until all is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips or chips of choice.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in two lengthwise; scoop out seeds and pulp. Stuff with stove-top stuffing prepared as box directions, except do not cook it before stuffing
the zucchini. Top with mozzarella cheese. Put zucchini in casserole with a little water. Cover casserole and bake at 350 degrees approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
In casserole dish, layer sliced potatoes and onion.
Put pork chops on top of potatoes and add soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
For a different taste, add 1 cup of Cheddar cheese.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix altogether and serve with fish.
(I use onion, chopped fine and bread and butter pickles, chopped fine.)

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and cook in buttered dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, peas and eggs.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
In a separate bowl, mix together mayonnaise and sugar.
Ice top layer of salad with mayo mixture.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, sugar, spices and beaten eggs together. Add baking powder, salt and flour.
Add warm water to put it together.
Roll cookies into small balls.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: opossum
directions: Clean opossum.
Dice garlic and onion.
Parboil until tender. Season with salt, pepper and red pepper.
Sprinkle garlic and onion over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Meat is greasy; eat only small amounts.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add eggs; mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder, sifted together.
Mix until well blended.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pineapple sheath cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured sheath cake pan (11 x 17-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a serving bowl, carefully combine pineapple, oranges, apple, bananas and marshmallows.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Add juices and mix well.
Cook mixture in top of double boiler over low heat until the consistency of custard, then chill.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour mixed with baking powder and then sour cream.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Line an 8 or 9-inch square pan (or 9 x 13-inch baking dish if you want thinner pieces) with foil or cooking spray.
If using foil, butter foil.

title: dawn's german skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, cook the bacon slices until crisp.
Remove the bacon from the skillet and drain on paper towel.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of the bacon drippings in the skillet.
To the skillet, add cabbage wedges, chopped onion, water, sugar, minced garlic and caraway seed.
Bring the liquid to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook the cabbage-onion mixture over medium-low heat for 10 minutes.

title: grandma's barbecue
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in shortening in saucepan.
Add corned beef, catsup and cinnamon; mix well.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Serve on buns.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak in strips and sprinkle with paprika. Let stand 5 minutes. In large skillet, melt butter and brown steak. Add garlic and broth. Cover and simmer on low for 30 minutes. Stir in onion and peppers. Cover and cook 5 more minutes. Mix flour, water and soy sauce. Stir in until thickened and serve over rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese on flat, round plate, adding 1 tablespoon horseradish and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Spread evenly. Spread chili sauce over cream cheese mixture.
Add shrimp and place evenly over chili sauce layer.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Triscuits or favorite crackers.

title: lois' tomato fish bake
directions: Sprinkle onion, celery and parsley in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place fish over vegetables.
Pour oil over fish. Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle more vegetables on top of the fish.
Pour tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Yields 6 servings.

title: christmas eve pasta(penne with peas and red bell pepper)
directions: Heat a large frying pan.
Add the olive oil, garlic, onions, bell pepper and parsley; saute until tender.
Bring a large pot of water with a pinch of salt to a boil.
In a small bowl, beat the eggs together with the half and half; set aside.
Place a colander in the sink; put the thawed peas in it.
Cook the pasta in the boiling salted water until al dente; drain it into the colander onto the peas (this will cook the peas sufficiently).
Return the drained pasta and peas to the pot; add the sauteed vegetables, basil, egg and half and half mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Toss this all together; serve immediately.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Beat until light and fluffy. Stir in sour cream and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Divide dough into thirds and work with 1/3 at a time.
Refrigerate extra dough. Roll out dough onto lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness. Press out with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Use a blender.
Pack dry ingredients down and blend.
Put in a quart jar and refrigerate.

title: layered cookies(golden brownies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in 9-inch square pan; tilt pan to cover bottom completely.
Sprinkle over butter in layers:
graham cracker crumbs, chopped nuts, chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels and flaked coconut.
Pour condensed milk evenly over top.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add all other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend ingredients and chill for 24 hours.

title: spice tea
directions: Steep the tea bags in 1 quart water.
Boil together the 2 3/4 cups sugar and 2 quarts water.
Mix together, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Heat all together until spices and juices have blended.
Remove spices. Serve hot.
Yields 30 cups.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Combine oleo, peanut butter, and sugar; mix well. Form into small balls. (About 1 inch diameter.) Melt chocolate chips in double boiler; using a toothpick, dip balls into chocolate. Place on wax paper to dry.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use Bundt pan and spray Pam cooking spray in bottom and sides of pan before cooking. Heat oven to 350°.
Put some of the nuts in bottom of pan. Quarter each can of biscuits and roll in mixture of white sugar and cinnamon.
Drop, do not press, biscuits down in pan until you have finished each can, mixing nuts throughout the layers.
Melt butter and brown sugar together in small saucepan, approximately 5 minutes, then pour immediately over biscuits in pan.
Cook for 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes, then invert onto plate.

title: grandma debrun's french cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg yolks; add to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla; mix well.
Stir in flour.
Chill overnight.
Drop by spoonfuls onto well-greased waffle iron.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes on high until golden.

title: chinese spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all other ingredients.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars together.
Add the egg and beat well.
Sift the remaining dry ingredients together and add to the first mixture.
Add the vanilla and form into small balls.
Place on a greased baking sheet and press each ball flat with the prongs of a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen (2-inch) cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in a 1 1/2 quart bowl.
Add syrup and mix well.
Beat eggs with fork.
Mix in milk, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell (unbaked).
Bake near center of 375° oven about 50 minutes or until firm.
Cool before serving.

title: crispy chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line shallow baking pan with aluminum foil.
Cut wings at each joint, discarding tips.
Melt shortening in lined pan.
Combine flour, onion salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add chicken pieces, a few at a time; shake to coat.
Place in pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Turn chicken wings over and bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes, or until crisp.
Transfer to paper towels before serving.
Serve with barbecue sauce, Blue cheese or hot sauce.
Makes about 32 to 36 pieces.

title: tadpole-in-a-hole
directions: Turn the oven to 400°. Put some shortening on a piece of paper towel or waxed
paper. Spread the shortening over the bottom and sides of the baking dish or pan to grease it.

title: punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Thaw 1 hour before serving and add 2 bottles of ginger ale.

title: nancy's potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in round pie plate.
Shred potatoes and let sit in cold water.
Mix potatoes with egg, salt and pepper. Gradually mix in flour and then pack into pie plate.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 40 minutes uncovered at 400°.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 10 minutes.
Garnish with green onions, bacon bits and sour cream.

title: quick chicken salad
directions: Mix to taste the diced chicken or turkey with Thousand Island dressing.
Serve in lettuce leaf and garnish with tomato.
Melba rounds are a great addition.

title: crumb cake
directions: Use hands to make crumbs out of oleo, brown sugar and flour. Reserve 1 cup for topping.

title: party chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, salad dressing, chilies, cheese and onion. Mix lightly.
Cover bread with chicken mixture.
Broil 5 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: spicy eggplant
directions: Fry eggplant until golden brown.
Drain.
Pour out all but 1 teaspoon of oil.
Stir-fry garlic 10 seconds.
Add ground pork or chicken, soy sauce, chicken broth and hoisin sauce.
Stir-fry until ground pork or chicken is browned.
Add vinegar and eggplant and toss lightly.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into pork and eggplant mixture.
Add green onions and stir-fry for 5 seconds. Makes 6 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a medium nonstick pan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.
Has 230 calories, fat free.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix first five ingredients in microwave bowl for 7 1/2 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Add soda and stir well.
Pour in 2 pie pans lined with foil.
Cool and enjoy.

title: spinach rice casserole
directions: Cook spinach just until tender; drain thoroughly.
Combine eggs, milk, cheese and rice.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Add spinach.
Pour into buttered, shallow, 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: blackened red fish
directions: Mix spice ingredients. Dip each fish fillet in melted butter and sprinkle with spice mixture; drop in very hot cast iron skillet. A tablespoon of butter may be added to hot skillet just before seasoned fish fillets are added to prevent sticking. Cook 3 to 4 minutes per side.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain all beans in large bowl.
Add onions.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Add salt.
Marinate 24 hours.
Will last 4 days refrigerated.

title: nettie mae's rolls
directions: Combine milk, sugar and shortening; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Mix yeast with warm water.
Combine all ingredients and mix.
Place damp cloth over mixture and refrigerate.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Use 2 teaspoons of mix to one cup of hot water.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in oil (3 minutes each side).
Add mushrooms, garlic, rosemary, tomatoes and wine.
Cook until most of the liquid is gone (about 15 minutes). Cover and cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Top with cheese and melt.

title: nacho supper
directions: Brown beef with chili powder and onions; drain.
Add all ingredients.
Heat and pour over nachos.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese while hot.

title: apple slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, apples and scallions.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill (3 hours).

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter with sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture to make smooth dough.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding as directed on the package with milk. Set aside. Mix together cream cheese and condensed milk. Add Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture to vanilla pudding. Mix well. Place layer of cookies on the bottom of rectangular dish. Place sliced bananas on top of cookies, spread vanilla pudding mixture on bananas and top with chessman cookies.

title: adobe bread(historical california recipe)
directions: Dissolve yeast and warm water in a bowl.
Add the oil and sugar.
Mix and let rest for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Knead until smooth, adding up to 3 cups white flour. Let rise until double.
Divide into 4 loaves.
Let rise 1/2 hour. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crust for fruit pie
directions: Sweeten fruit while cold.
Bake at 375°.
Melt oleo and pour fruit over and then pour crust over the fruit.

title: keebler bars
directions: In microwave dish, mix butter, milk and sugars.
Melt; stir. Add graham cracker crumbs.
Bring to boil.
Line 9 x 13-inch dish with Club crackers, salt side up.
Spread graham cracker mixture over crackers.
Layer another layer of Club crackers over top of mixture.
Microwave peanut butter, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips until melted.
Spread evenly over Club crackers.
Refrigerate to set approximately 2 hours.

title: pork chops with tortellini
directions: Place pork chops on rack in broiler pan.
Broil until well done, turning once.
Cook pasta in salted, boiling water following package directions; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add pasta, salt, pepper, rosemary and sage.
Heat thoroughly, shaking pan frequently.
Place pasta on heated serving platter.
Place pork on pasta.
Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, salt, pepper, salad oil and vinegar.
Add green pepper, onion, radishes, green beans, yellow beans and kidney beans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over cabbage and onion.
Will keep in fridge for three weeks.

title: parmesan potato wedges
directions: Line a baking sheet with heavy duty foil.
Cut each potato into eight wedges; place on foil.
Coat with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Thaw La creme.
Mix in dry pudding.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 teaspoon of flavoring.
Tastes best when refrigerated for a day.
Serve with fruit, such as bananas, strawberries and cantaloup.

title: cheese rice crispy
directions: Mix grated cheese and oleo.
Add flour and mix well.
Add cereal and mix well.
Shape into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each ball with a fork and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients except for cheese. Pour half of mixture into a well-greased pan.
Sprinkle on all cheese.
Add remaining mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar and Crisco.
Add molasses and vinegar.
Combine flour, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add alternately with the soda and water to the creamed mixture.
On a lightly floured board, roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter or a drinking glass dipped in flour. Place on greased baking sheets approximately 1-inch apart.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: brenda's lite strawberry cake
directions: Slice strawberries. Sprinkle Sweet & Low packets over strawberries. Add 1/4 cup water to strawberries with wooden spoon until sweetener is dissolved. Set aside. Beat cake mix, oil and eggs on high speed until blended, then gradually add water to mixture until smooth. Bake in 9 x 13 inch pan at 350 degrees for 30 minutes until done. After cake is cooled to the touch, poke with a fork and make holes in cake, spoon strawberries over cake top. Chill in refrigerator. After cake has chilled, dollop Cool Whip down the center of cake length of cake. Carefully spread to sides with a spoon.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in given order.
Bake in 3 greased bread pans at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk; beat until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch cake pan or 9 x 13-inch or 2-quart casserole baking dish.
Spoon drained cherries over batter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Pour fruit juice and water (1 cup) over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and peppers
directions: Split chicken breasts in half.
Dredge in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in skillet.
Brown chicken breasts in butter.
Remove to a shallow, covered, baking dish.
Saute peppers until limp.
Add to chicken.
Add wine to skillet and cook for a minute, scraping bottom of pan with a wooden spoon.
Remove skillet from heat, add herbs to wine and pour over chicken.
Cover baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, basting once or twice during cooking.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 4 g, protein 15 g, fat 18 g, calories 270.

title: magic salmon mold
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Place salmon in bottom of mold.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Add 1 1/4 cups cold water, vinegar, lemon juice and salt. Pour half of gelatin over salmon.
Chill until set.
Fill mold with alternating layers of cabbage and eggs.
Cover with remaining gelatin.
Chill until set.

title: quick, no-bake melt-in-your-mouth, cool, refreshing, fruit yogurt
directions: *May be sprinkled over the top and/or garnished with additional strawberries, if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add melted butter; add sugar, syrup, pecans and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 300°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook, stirring often to prevent scorching, until thick (30 to 45 minutes).
Hot bath 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding(25 people)
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Bake in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans at 350° for about 1 hour or until a knife comes clean when placed in it.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Roll on floured surface and cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° until just set.
Do not overbake.

title: pumpkin chess pie
directions: Process pumpkin and next 9 ingredients in container of an electric blender or food processor until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Pour pumpkin mixture into prepared pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together into a large bowl.
Make a hole in center.
Add pumpkin, oil, eggs and water.
Mix well, bake at 350° for one hour.
Let cool for a few minutes in pan and then put in refrigerator overnight for 24 hours.
It keeps well and freezes well.

title: granny's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Prepare your favorite flaky pie crust. Beat eggs well in medium bowl. Add next 4 ingredients, beating until well blended. Arrange pecans in bottom of pie crust and carefully pour mixture over them. Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted from edge comes out clean. Allow to cool. Serves 8.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan; add chopped onions.
Stir and cook a few minutes.
Add beef bouillon, 1 cup uncooked rice and mushrooms. Stir well; pour into casserole dish.
Cover; cook in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until rice absorbs the liquid.

title: ruth's rice krispie cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix together margarine, granulated sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir dry ingredients and creamed mixture together.
Mix in Rice Krispies, oatmeal and chopped walnuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: drop apies cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Refrigerate.
Drop on cookie sheet, leaving a big space between.
Put chopped nuts on top and press down.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown around edge.

title: carmelitas
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Press half of mixture in a 9 x 13 greased pan. Bake 10-15 minutes at 350°.
Mix caramel and flour.
Spread over oatmeal base, and sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Then top with the rest of oatmeal mixture.
Bake an additional 20-25 minutes until golden.
Let cool before cutting.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into individual serving dishes or large serving bowl.
Chill 30 minutes. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: white hot sauce
directions: Mix in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Put in jar and refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in large bowl.
Add cranberry sauce to Jell-O in small amounts.
Whisk until cranberry sauce is melted.
Whisk in sour cream.
Pour into mold.
Spray with Pam.

title: microwave whitefish
directions: Place whitefish in glass pie plate.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, garlic salt or powder and paprika to taste.
Place margarine pats on fish.
Slice small onion on top.
Cover with wax paper and heat in microwave on High for 7 to 10 minutes, depending on thickness of fish.
It's done when fish is flaky.

title: dinner salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and gelatin with 2 cups boiling water. Refrigerate until partially set.
Add fruit; fold in Cool Whip. Fill mold and chill until thick.

title: easy hawaiian supper
directions: Drain pineapple juice into measuring cup and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Combine liquid, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in bowl; set aside.
Heat margarine in large skillet.
Saute ham, chicken, green pepper, scallions and garlic powder until chicken is lightly browned.
Stir in liquid mixture and bring to boil.
Stir in pineapple and rice, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and allspice in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, combine pumpkin and milk.
Add oil, sugar and egg; beat until fluffy.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture, beating well.
Fold in raisins.
Fill paper lined muffin cups almost full.
Bake for about 30 to 35 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Toothpick inserted in center should come out clean.
Makes about 18.

title: apple oat crisp
directions: In a small bowl mix apples, applesauce, sweetener, lemon juice, 1/4 tsp. cinnamon, and sugar.
Scrape into an 8-inch square pan sprayed with Pam.
In a small bowl mix oats, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, and margarine.
Mix until crumbly; sprinkle evenly over apple mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350.
Divide into 4 servings.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix and Jell-O.
Add oil, water and lemon extract. Add eggs, dropping in 2 at a time.
Beat for 2 minutes, then drop 2 more and beat for 2 more minutes.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes in tube pan.
Put on frosting while hot.

title: aunt selma's spoon bread
directions: Gradually stir the corn meal into the milk.
Let this come to a boil, making mush. Add the salt and butter to the hot mush.
Add the eggs and baking powder.
Pour mixture into casserole. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Serve from baking dish.

title: curried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl, then add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients and bring to boil.
Cook one minute. Remove from heat and stir in next 3 ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer bananas and cookies in a 9 x 13-inch pan (or whatever you want).
Fill pan to the top with banana and cookie layers. Mix sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan.
Add milk and egg yolks. Mix well.
Stir over heat constantly until pudding thickens (low heat); add vanilla.
Remove from heat and pour over cookies and bananas.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, Doritos and cheese.
In casserole dish, put layer of Doritos, layer of soup mixture, layer of chicken and layer of cheese.
Repeat and top with cheese.

title: lemon tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours before serving.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cheese and jello.
Mix thoroughly and drain fruit.
Add to other ingredients; mix well.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: congealed dessert
directions: Dissolve the jello according to directions.
Put in refrigerator until begins congealing.
Add fruit and marshmallows. Let congeal until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done; remove from bone.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix soup, milk and 1/2 cup of broth; pour over chicken. Prepare stuffing, onion, margarine and 1/2 cup broth by mixing together; spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Grate 3 lemon rinds.
Scrape side of grater.
Use 1/2 cup water to wash side of grater.
Separate yolk and white from eggs. Add egg yolks, cornstarch, sugar and water to rind mixture.
Cook until thick.
If not thick enough, mix cornstarch and water; add to mixture to thicken.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Put on pies to make meringue.
Put in oven to brown meringue.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add Rice Krispies. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: roast beef with mushroom gravy
directions: Mix 2 teaspoons thyme, 1 teaspoon pepper and garlic powder. Rub mixture all over the roast.
Place roast on microwave-safe roasting rack with sides and shield cut edges with foil. Microwave, uncovered, on Medium-low 30 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn twice during cooking.
Remove foil; turn roast over. Microwave 7 to 10 minutes longer until cooked.
Sprinkle with salt and remove roast to a platter.
Cover meat loosely with foil and let stand 15 minutes.
Save pan juice for gravy.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Melt the two packages of chips.
Add nuts and noodles.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: maple nut fudge candy
directions: Mix sugar, cream, syrup and butter. Stir constantly while boiling for 12 minutes. Take off heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in flavoring, marshmallow cream and nuts. Stir until thick enough to pour into buttered pan. When cool, cut in squares.

title: chunky peanut brittle
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with aluminum foil and spray lightly with Pam. Sprinkle with 1 cup of peanut butter pieces. In a heavy 2-quart pan, heat sugar, syrup, oleo and water to boiling. Cook to 300° (to a hard-crack) over medium heat. Remove from heat and stir in chopped peanuts. Pour immediately onto cookie sheet and spread over the entire area. Sprinkle with chocolate pieces and remaining peanut butter pieces. When they have melted enough, spread over entire pan with a knife, covering all edges carefully. Cool until hard and break into small pieces.

title: fruity salad
directions: Add jello and boiling water; mix.
Then add cold water and chill.
Add can of crushed pineapple, reserving liquid.
Ad sliced bananas, cans of oranges and mini marshmallows.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter; blend in 2 tablespoons flour.
Combine sugar, pineapple juice and egg.
Add to flour mixture and cook until thick.
Allow to cool; spread over jello.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: crab 'n spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saut onion, green pepper and mushrooms in margarine in skillet.
Add tomatoes, crabmeat, sour cream and spaghetti. Mix gently.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: devil's food pudding cake
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together and place in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Stir in water and add marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix as directed on the package.
Spoon batter carefully over sugar and marshmallow mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Turn over 10 minutes after removing from oven so that mixture runs over cake.
Yields about 16 to 20 servings.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes; pierce several times with fork.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Cut in halves lengthwise, scoop out pulp; discard jackets.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Add flour; cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Cook for 1 minute longer.
Add milk gradually; cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onions, 1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup cheese. Cook until heated through.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve topped with remaining green onions, bacon and cheese.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Crumble Bleu cheese into other ingredients.
Mix with fork. Yield: 1 pint.
This will taste just as good or better than any restaurant dressing.

title: raspberry bombe
directions: Chill a 2 1/2-quart mold in freezer.
Stir sherbet to soften. With spoon, spread sherbet thickly over the sides and bottom of the mold.
Freeze firm.
Spread ice cream into the mold over top of the sherbet, covering completely.
Freeze firm.
Mix the Cool Whip, sugar and salt, then add the fruits, nuts and flavoring. Pile into the center of the mold, smoothing the top.
Cover with foil and freeze.
Peel off foil and invert mold onto a plate. Serve cold.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix the pudding with 2 1/4 cups milk.
Refrigerate.
Add 3/4 cup Kahlua.
Make any chocolate cake mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Let cool.
Cut cake into layers and put pudding mix and candy between layers.
Top with Cool Whip and more Skor bar candy.

title: mrs. stephenson's sheet cake and chocolate icing
directions: Sift flour; measure and re-sift with salt and sugar.
In a saucepan, put water, butter and cocoa; bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture.
In another bowl, beat eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to other mixture; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add molasses, egg, spices and dry ingredients.
Do not overbeat.
Refrigerate.
Roll into balls. Smash (kid's will love to help!) with bottom of glass dipped in water.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes, just until they are chewy. You will have to experiment with your oven and what you like.

title: party potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add milk if needed.
Beat in rest of ingredients until light and fluffy.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.
Dot with butter, then bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat.
Drain well.
Add next three ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Season to taste (salt and pepper).
Add sauce and mix together.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish. Top with favorite grated cheese.
Cover with crescent rolls, rolled flat or leave plain.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lite lemon cheesecake
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle bottom and sides with graham cracker crumbs.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, pour into blender container; add cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Blend at medium speed about 2 minutes or until completely smooth.
Pour into large bowl.
Gently stir in thawed Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared pan.
Chill until set (4 hours).
When ready to serve, top with pie filling.

title: green rice
directions: Chop bell pepper, onions, and jalapeno peppers.
Saute in butter.
Add bouillon cubes, 1 cup rice and water.
Let stand until moisture is gone.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine corn, green pepper, celery, tomato and salt with French dressing; chill.
Serve on salad greens; garnish with onion rings, if desired.

title: chicken in white wine
directions: Split or quarter chickens, depending on size.
Cook onions and garlic in 1/2 cup water and 2 tablespoons butter for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Mix dressing and next 8 ingredients.
Layer dressing, chicken, dressing and chicken in casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake 40 minutes at 325° in covered dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: french toast
directions: Slice French bread on angel into 1-inch slices; set aside. Beat all ingredients together.
Dip and coat bread slices.
Place in skillet which is over medium to medium high heat.
Flip once and serve with butter and syrup or powdered lightly with powdered sugar.

title: oyster crackers snack
directions: Shake crackers and dry ingredients in a doubled brown grocery bag.
Drizzle 1 cup oil (slightly less) in the bag; shake carefully until all is covered.
(Oiliness disappears.)

title: pistachio salad
directions: Put dry pudding in large bowl.
Add pineapple and mix thoroughly.
Add marshmallows and stir.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill.

title: katie's sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Place in large saucepan.
Cover with boiling water; bring back to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered about 30 minutes.
Drain; let cool.
Peel and halve lengthwise.
In large skillet, combine butter, salt, sugar and 1/4 cup water; stir over low heat until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
Boil uncovered 3 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Add potatoes and pecans; simmer uncovered 5 minutes, basting often with syrup.
Serve potatoes with syrup and nuts spooned over them.

title: quick pecan bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: scotcha-roos
directions: In a large pan combine syrup and sugar.
Bring just to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter. Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into a greased pan.
Mix morsels and melt over low heat.
Spread over the Rice Krispies.

title: chilled sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the first 2 ingredients and put into an oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Mix together the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip. Spread on crust.
Cool slightly.
Mix together the margarine, sweet potatoes, vanilla, 1 cup sugar and egg and spread over the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Place bacon and cheese in pie shell; mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour the mixed ingredients over the bacon and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: miracle whip
directions: *I use 1/2 cup clear jel.

title: sesame steak
directions: In skillet over medium heat, warm salad oil and cook sesame seed until golden.
Slice onions thickly.
In baking dish, mix sesame seed, oil and onions.
Add soy sauce, wine, sugar, pepper and garlic. Marinate meat in mixture for 8 hours or more, turning occasionally.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix in skillet.
Add slowly about 3 or 4 cups milk, stirring to mix.
Cook until thickness desired.
Stir constantly over low heat.
When done, add 1/2 stick butter.

title: tomato swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip steak pieces in mixture. Cover evenly.
Place steak pieces in Dutch oven on top of stove.

title: ginger cream cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with water.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.
(Watch carefully that they don't burn; if seems too hot, turn oven to 375°.) While slightly warm, frost with Confectioners Icing.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Line bottom of pan with aluminum foil and butter well.
Bring ingredients to a boil over medium heat; stirring constantly until golden brown (5 to 6 minutes).
Pour into pan.
Cool; break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and butter.
Mix well.
Add water and egg yolks.
Beat with mixer.
Cook until thick and add vanilla.
Pour into prepared shells.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese spread until smooth.
Stir in the other ingredients.
Spoon into a small ovenproof dish that has been sprayed with a non-fat cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 2 cups (eight 1/4-cup servings).

title: guacamole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Mix well and place in bowl. Spread top with mayonnaise, sealing to edges of bowl. At serving time, stir in mayonnaise. Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix milk, sugar and eggs together.
Pour over corn.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put spots of butter over top and bake at 450 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in greased casserole dish.
Add soups and milk. Melt margarine and pour over stuffing mix, which has been sprinkled over chicken.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Add ingredients, mixing well.
Spread light cover of oil to prevent crust over top while rising.
Let rise 8 to 10 hours until double in size.
Punch down and make out into 3 to 4 loaves. Makes 3 large or 4 small loaves of bread.
You will need to add enough bread flour just to be able to work bread.
Make out into loaves and put in greased pans.
Let rise until reaches top of pan, 8 hours approximately.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown and touches done.
(This is delicious with raisins and/or pecans.)
When cooked, drizzle sugar and water mixture over top of loaves.

title: cornpone pie
directions: Simmer ground beef, chopped onion, oil and salt.
While meat is simmering, stir up crust.
Add Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce and kidney beans to cooked meat mixture.

title: lazy woman's cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in oven dish.
Set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, milk, sugar and salt.
Pour on top of melted margarine. Do not mix.
Pour fruit in the middle of the flour mixture.
Do not mix.
Sprinkle cinnamon and dash of nutmeg over fruit.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: jiffy orange coffeecake* * * * *
directions: The first time I had quiche was in a little town in Switzerland.
It was so good, I wanted to eat the whole pie.
It was served with a salad, wonderful homemade bread and French Silk Pie.

title: hamburg casserole with chow mein noodles
directions: Brown hamburg and onions.
Add celery, soups, rice, water and soy sauce.
Bake 1/2 hour covered at 350°; bake 1/2 hour uncovered.
Cover with 1 small can chow mein noodles the last 15 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream lard and sugar; add eggs and bananas.
Add dry ingredients quickly and mix.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: veal piccata
directions: Flatten each cutlet.
Dredge lightly with flour.
Heat butter in a large skillet.
When very hot, saute veal over high heat until browned lightly, about 1 minute on each side.
It needs very little cooking.
Remove from heat and keep warm.
Add wine and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil, scraping browned sides.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over veal and serve.
I add about 2 tablespoons pesto sauce.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook and bone chicken and place in baking dish.
Put mushrooms over chicken.
Mix sour cream and soup together; pour over chicken and mushrooms.
Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Add poppy seed.
Put over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; add egg yolks and mix well. Add blackberry jam.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and baking powder to flour.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to cake mixture.
Add chopped nuts and raisins.
Last, fold in the beaten egg whites.
The batter will be very stiff (may have to use hands to mix ingredients).

title: raspberry smoothies
directions: In a blender, combine all the ingredients. Cover and process until well blended. Pour into chilled glasses. Serve immediately. Yield: 3 servings.

title: jessica's chicken
directions: Wrap 1 slice bacon around each piece of chicken.
Place side by side in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in a 225° oven for 3 1/2 hours.
Garnish with mushrooms and parsley. Serve with rice.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine well.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan, pressing mixture up sides to form crust.
Beat remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Spread over crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool, cut into small squares.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Pour flour in bowl.
Cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cheese.
Add buttermilk; stir just until dough clings together.
On lightly floured surface, knead dough lightly until easy to handle.
Roll into a 12-inch circle.
Cut into 8 wedges.
Begin at wide end of wedge and roll toward point.
Place biscuits, point side down, on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield: 8 biscuits.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat with onions, peppers, salt, pepper and onion powder. Add chili brick, tomatoes and paste.
Add chili beans, celery and chili powder (if used).
Simmer 1 hour or more in very large pot.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie crusts. Refrigerate.
Will keep several days.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour in baking dish. Mix last 4 ingredients and pour over top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: meatless pepper stuffing
directions: If you use a meat flavored rice, hamburger (fried and crumbled) can also be used.

title: pork loin with roasted sweet potatoes and parsnips
directions: *Carrots may be substituted for parsnips.

title: preserved fun
directions: Mix the children and dogs; put them in a field which is well fenced, stirring occasionally.
Pour the brook over pebbles.
Add flowers to garnish.
Spread over all a deep blue sky.
Bake in hot sun.
Do this every day in summer, cooling children in tub once a day.
Preserved in this way, the memory of childhood on the farm lasts indefinitely.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Combine and mix well whipped topping and yogurt.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with an extra twist of whipped topping and garnish with fruit, if desired. Enjoy!

title: meat balls(frikadeller)
directions: Mix the first six ingredients thoroughly.
Add eggs, milk and margarine.
Form into patties and fry in butter at 300° (electric skillet) until brown.
Turn down heat to 250° and cover for 30 minutes to thoroughly cook.

title: okra casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in tomato, okra and basil. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly. Turn into 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until warmed through. Serve with crackers.

title: fruit salad supreme
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Beat dry vanilla pudding with juice for 1 minute.
Add sour cream.
Blend in topping.
Fold all fruit into dressing and chill several hours before serving.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Combine water and butter; bring to a boil.
Add broccoli and simmer 5 minutes.
Add uncooked rice; cover pan and set aside 5 minutes.
Then stir in undiluted soup and melted Cheez Whiz.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: brewer's congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix and add the other ingredients.
Pour into Pyrex dish.
Congeal and serve.

title: zesty sausage
directions: Cut smoked sausage into chunks.
Combine all ingredients in a medium size saucepan.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Can be served over rice.

title: white fudge
directions: Cook and stir first 2 ingredients on low heat to a full-boil approximately 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat in the jar of peanut butter, 1 tablespoon margarine and Marshmallow Creme.
Pour into a buttered dish or pan.

title: marinade for cauliflower or other vegetables
directions: Mix together; pour over prepared raw cauliflower.
Marinate for at least 2 hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and stir for 2 minutes.
In a baking pan, add butter and pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: fish cakes
directions: Make into cakes, flour and fry in hot oil.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, melted margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix well and spread in oblong baking dish.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Brown and cook chicken strips in oil.
Saute onion, peppers and mushrooms in soy sauce.
Place desired amount of cooked chicken on 1/2 of the tortilla shell.
Top chicken with desired amount of onion, peppers and mushrooms.
Add some Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Fold 1/2 of tortilla shell over chicken mixture.
Press ends of shell with fork.
Microwave or place in oven to melt cheese.
Shells can be browned before fixing.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cook and drain noodles according to package instructions; drain. Heat butter and whipping cream in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, stirring frequently, until butter is melted and mixture starts to boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer 6 minutes, stirring frequently, until slightly thickened. Remove from heat. Stir in cheese, salt and pepper. Pour sauce over noodles. Toss until well coated.

title: "hello dolly cookies"
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and pecan halves.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over all ingredients.
Do not stir at any time. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put ham in small plastic bag and shape into ball.
Place in freezer until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Let cheese soften at room temperature. When ham is firm, mold cream cheese around ham ball, then roll in shredded Cheddar cheese.
Return to refrigerator until firm.
To serve, place on platter or cheese board and surround with crackers.

title: diet mincemeat cake
directions: Mix mincemeat, egg, Equal, coffee, syrup and Crisco; beat well.
Add soda and flour.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sesame green beans
directions: Golden brown sesame seeds.
Cook beans until crisp; drain. Return to saucepan with soy and salad oil.
Cook 10 minutes longer to blend flavors.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Serve warm or cold.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, then flour.
Beat well. Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until good and tender.

title: tracey's banana split pie
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter. Press into bottom of tall glass bowl as the crust.

title: strawberry frozen pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Reserve 1/2 cup of berries and syrup.
Add remaining berries and syrup to cheese mixture. Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 5 minutes before serving.
Cut in wedges.
Serve topped with reserved berries in syrup.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix tang and milk. Add sour cream and vanilla. Mix well.
Add topping. Pour in graham cracker crust. Decorate top with Mandarin oranges.

title: creamy baked cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
