Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and real lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer. Cool.
Serve with Raspberry Topping or any of your favorite fruit toppings.

title: coconut krispies
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar, dates and beaten egg.
Stir constantly for 5 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat, add vanilla, Rice Krispies and walnuts.
With greased hands, form balls and then roll in coconut.
Place on wax paper to cool. Yields between 24 to 48, depending on size of ball.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix ingredients into an 8 x 10-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: weenie beanie burger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Cut up hot dogs into 8 to 10 pieces per hot dog.
Combine browned ground beef, cut up hot dogs and baked beans (undrained).
Pour into a small casserole dish (approximately 8 x 8-inch).
Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into the prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until mixture has set.
Let cool slightly, then cut into squares.
This may be served warm or cool and may be reheated in the microwave.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
In a separate bowl, mix the pudding, milk and vanilla.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt margarine and add flour to make a roux or gravy base. Then add onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic and cook for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice with hot bread.

title: everybody's favorite chocolate chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: chili(firefighters like it hot)
directions: In large heavy skillet, cook meat, onions and pepper until meat is brown and vegetables tender.
Drain kidney beans, reserve liquid.
Add beans and other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add bean liquid for right consistency, then add spaghetti and cook.
Serves 10.

title: butter bean pie
directions: Layer ingredients, except Mexican corn bread in order given. Mix Mexican corn bread.
Spread on top for crust.
Bake until corn bread is done.

title: crushed pineapple 3 layer cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Place in 3 cake pans.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: krispy kookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop cookies on slightly oiled cookie sheets (PAM spray).
Bake at 350° from 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon swirl frosting *
directions: *A not too sweet frosting.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour contents of pork and beans in a saucepan; add molasses, mustard, catsup, onions and Worcestershire and mix.
Cook half of bacon and cut into small pieces and mix into mixture.
Top with remaining bacon and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and serve.

title: plantation shrimp pileau
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Save 3 teaspoons drippings.
Crumble bacon. Combine water, salt and drippings in large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; reduce heat.
Cover; cook 20 minutes. Sprinkle shrimp with Worcestershire sauce, then dredge in flour. Saute shrimp, celery and green pepper for 3 minutes.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in rice.
Add salt, pepper and bacon, stirring well.
Serve hot.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix. Spread in pie plate (sprayed with Pam).
Beat eggs, milk and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheeses and bake additional 10 minutes.
Top with diced tomatoes.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: angel cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Cook in muffin pans at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, flour and powdered sugar, the first three. Pat into a 9 x 13 inch greased pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and blend. Add milk and salt. Cook until slightly thick, stirring constantly.
Add 2 cups diced, cooked potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes on very low heat, stirring occasionally.
Thin if necessary with a little potato water or milk.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, covered, at 350°.
Uncover for additional 10 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: In small double boiler, set over simmering water or a heavy saucepan, melt chocolate, stirring often until chocolate is smooth and reaches 90°.
Meanwhile on a baking sheet, arrange 24 of marshmallows in a single layer in blocks of six.
Cut the remaining marshmallows into eighths.
Place into the saucepan.
When chocolate is ready, pour about 1/4 cup, enough to cover over each block.
White streaks in chocolate mean too hot.
Stir about 1/2 cup of the melted chocolate into pecans.
Keep warm.
Stir marshmallows pieces into remaining chocolate.
Put pecan mixture over marshmallows.
Spread on top of marshmallows.
Let stand until set.
To serve, break or cut candy into pieces.
Makes about 1 3/4 pounds of candy.

title: pepperoni alfredo
directions: Cook fettucini; keep warm.
Melt butter in large skillet. Stir in half and half, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook and stir 5 minutes, or until it starts to thicken.
Stir in cheese; cook over low heat just until melted, stirring constantly.
Immediately stir in pepperoni and fettucini; toss to coat with sauce.

title: not so sweet chocolate icing
directions: Blend shortening, egg, cocoa and salt.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Mix well until smooth.
Add more sugar or milk to make icing thin or thick.

title: harvest loaf or pumpkin chocolate chip bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Place in prepared loaf pan, lightly greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can top with mixture of cinnamon, sugar and chopped nuts prior to cooking. Tastes extra special!

title: elephant stew("just for fun")
directions: Cut 1 medium-sized elephant into small bite-sized pieces. Brown in hot pan in which fat has been melted.
Add enough liquid to cover.
Liquid may be flavored with vegetable juice of most any kind available.
Cook over low heat, about 4 weeks.
Serves 3,800 people.
If more are expected, add 2 rabbits.
However, add rabbits only, if necessary, as most people don't care for hare (hair) in their stew.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 teaspoon soda and shake cream of tartar.
Pop 1 cup popcorn.
Pour mixture over popped corn.
Stir well, then spread on cookie sheets and place in warm oven at 275° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Turn onto waxed paper to cool.
Store in Tupperware or tight tins.

title: captain's salad
directions: Combine greens, onion rings and sesame seed. Toss and refrigerate until just before serving.

title: garlic dressing
directions: Blend together, add more buttermilk if thick.
Prepare day before for best results and flavor.

title: man's cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add coconut, nuts and oatmeal.
Mix all ingredients together, stirring well.
Chill overnight and roll in walnut size. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lime jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Let set in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Beat softened cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add pineapple with juice.
Pour slightly thickened jello in and put into mold.
Chill.

title: chocolate-peanut butter fudgies with oats
directions: Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: To Serve:
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons to one cup boiling water.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes, add other ingredients and mix together; put into casserole dish.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Place sliced potatoes in a casserole dish. Sprinkle with flour.
Pour milk over potatoes and flour.
Dot with 3 tablespoons butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with onions and dot with remaining butter.
Cook, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add beaten egg, sugar substitute and milk.
Sift and mix dry ingredients and then add to first mixture.
Beat in vanilla, raisins and rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields 30 cookies.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
Add the sugar, salt and butter; let cool.
Crumble the yeast and add water to soften.
Add to the lukewarm milk mixture.
Add 1/2 the flour and beat until smooth.
Add enough of the remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes after shaping in balls.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: lemon fizz salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water in a large bowl.
Add pineapple; chill until partially set.
Add next 3 ingredients and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Combine the sugar, flour, egg and juice in saucepan, mixing well.
Add butter. Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly; cool. Fold whipped cream into cooled mixture.
Spread over congealed layer.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: italian eggs
directions: Place bread in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix the rest of the ingredients. Pour over bread and refrigerate overnight. Set out 1/2 hour before baking. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frosted carrot bars
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Alternately add oil and flour.
Mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Spread evenly in jelly roll pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: apple salad (2)
directions: Add 2 tsp. lemon juice to apples so they won't brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put ingredients (except soda) in heavy saucepan.
Cook on low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook until syrup slightly changes color and a few peanuts pop.
Stir in soda and pour out on buttered pan.
Put butter on fingers and when barely cool enough to touch, lift from pan and stretch out thin.

title: pumpkin pie(good and gluten-free)
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugars, salt, spices and milks.
Butter a 9-inch pie plate generously.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Pour pumpkin mixture over cornmeal.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool and cut.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: Mix flour, butter and salt. Mix yolk with milk and add to flour mixture. Roll out half the dough and line bottom and sides of a 12 x 17-inch pan. Sprinkle with cornflakes. Top with apples. Combine sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle on top of apples. Roll remaining dough and seal on top. Beat egg whites until frothy and brush on crust. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes. Combine 1 cup powdered sugar and a little milk and drizzle on top while still warm.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain each can of vegetables. Boil sugar, oil and vinegar and cool. Pour over vegetables overnight.

title: party chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine chicken, peas, celery, water chestnuts, almonds, green pepper, onion and olives.
Sprinkle with wine, lemon juice and salt.
Mix gently.
In small saucepan combine milk and soup.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add to casserole mixture and blend well. Place in oven for about 20 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with bread cubes, return to oven to toast bread cubes.
Remove and sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bubble bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan. Place balls in pan, about 1/2 full.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and pudding.
Sprinkle over the balls.
Drizzle the melted oleo over all.
Cover with damp cloth and let stand overnight at room temperature.
To raise faster, leave off damp cloth.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry surprise cake
directions: Mix jello according to directions on package.
Let set in refrigerator until thick; do not jell.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Add pound cake, cut in squares.
Press into jello mixture, then completely jell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Add shrimp, onion, pepper strips and celery. Cook and stir until shrimp are pink. Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, hot pepper sauce, thyme and garlic powder. Bring to a boil. Stir in the rice; cover and remove from heat. Let stand for 5 or 6 minutes, then fluff with a fork. If desired, sprinkle with parsley before serving. Serve with garden salad and French bread.

title: oven-fried chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a shallow bowl, combine the bread crumbs, Parmesan, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Place the melted butter in another shallow bowl.
Dip the chicken pieces in the butter, then roll the pieces in the crumb mixture.
Put them in the baking dish.
Pour the remaining butter evenly over the chicken and bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Slice bread in half longway.
Spread with margarine on each half.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Sprinkle generously with grated Jack cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: tom thumb cookie bars
directions: Combine shortening and salt. Add 1/2 cup brown sugar and cream thoroughly. Add 1 cup of flour and blend. Spread mixture in greased and floured 8 x 12-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 325° or until delicately browned.

title: southwest party sandwiches
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Spread on your choice of dark bread.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, soy sauce, beans and 2/3 cup onions in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot. Stir. Sprinkle with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: green bean relish
directions: Boil beans in salt water and drain.
Boil other ingredients together and pour over beans.
Can in hot jars.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar slowly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flavoring.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Blend in above ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients slowly with above mixture, adding buttermilk slowly.
Last part of buttermilk, add vinegar and then add to the mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Use bacon drippings.
Add vinegar, water, salt, pepper and mustard.
Boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over hot and serve.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook, until it boils, the berries, sugar and salt.
Add cornstarch dissolved in water.
Cool and put in crusts.
Bake at 425° until crust is done, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: old-fashioned dewberry pie
directions: Pour washed, drained berries into an unbaked pie shell (approximately 1 1/2 cups).
Mix eggs, sugar, flour and milk and pour over the berries.
Top with margarine, flour and sugar mixture.
Mix until crumbly and sprinkle on top of pie. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until topping is browned.

title: grammie's ziti bake
directions: Cook and drain ziti; set aside.
Brown hamburg.
Remove from heat and add Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, egg, salt and pepper and half of sauce.
Add ziti.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add the remaining sauce and cover with Mozzarella.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: swiss baked chicken
directions: Using butter or margarine, grease the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place boneless chicken breasts in pan; season with salt and pepper as desired; cover with slices of Swiss cheese.
In a small bowl, add 1/4 cup of water to cream of chicken soup.
Blend and spread over chicken and Swiss cheese; sprinkle with bread crumbs or dry stuffing.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock pot meat dish
directions: Stir well.
Cook in crock pot for 4 hours on high or 6-7 hours on low.
Stir occasionally.

title: marzetti
directions: Cook meat the night before.
Put in refrigerator to cool. Don't pour off juices!!
Cut meat off bone into small pieces.
Put broth, meat and chopped onion in a large pot.
Make sure all fat is cut off.
Bring to boil.
Add tomatoes and puree.
Add 1/2 cheese (cut into small chunks).
Add noodles.
When noodles are cooked, add rest of cheese.
Stir and serve.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch pecan bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add vanilla and mix until blended. Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix on low speed until well blended.
Add nuts.
Spread evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325°
for 25 minutes, or until done when tested with toothpick.

title: mandarin cream salad
directions: Dissolve 2 packages Jell-O in 2 1/2 cups boiling water; add mandarin syrup.
Chill until thick; add mandarins.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan; chill until set.
Dissolve remaining package of Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Mix in ice cream by spoonfuls until melted; add bananas.
Chill until mixture mounds on spoon; spoon onto top of congealed layer.
Chill until firm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chili corn carne
directions: Brown ground meat slightly with onion and garlic in a saucepan.
Add seasonings, soup and kidney beans.
Cover and cook slowly for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with crisp crackers and relishes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rigatoni with tuna
directions: Serves 6 to 8. Cook rigatoni al dente and drain.
Let stand at least 1 hour until dry.
When pasta is dry, drain tuna, halve and seed tomatoes by squeezing together to discard seeds.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand 1 hour.
Adjust seasonings if necessary.

title: brown sugar nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Add sifted flour and baking powder.
Beat well; then add vanilla and nuts. Save some for top decoration.
Bake in a square pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ice with buttercream icing.
Decorate with remaining nuts.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Put on top crust (slitting several times for steam escape). Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: caitee's favorite frozen fruit salad
directions: Place oil, vinegar, onion, apple juice, mustard, cumin and hot pepper sauce in a mixing bowl; blend well.
Add the beans, corn, red pepper and cilantro and toss.
Chill 20 minutes or more. Bring to room temperature before serving.

title: one-bowl dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add softened margarine.
Slowly add hot water to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping often.
Add egg and another 1/2 cup flour or enough to make batter thick.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
With spoon, stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top cover.
Let rise in warm place, until doubled in bulk (about 1 hour).
Punch dough down.
Turn out onto floured board.
Shape into balls of desired size.
Place in greased pan rolling each so top is greased lightly.
Bake in hot 400° oven about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix. Cover with strips of bacon and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice krispies marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted and well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; stir well.
Place in pan and let cool.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Combine sugar, juice, vinegar and spices.
Bring to a boil and simmer ten minutes; add fruit and heat thoroughly.
Remove and refrigerate.

title: italian bean soup
directions: Soak beans.
Boil beans until soft.
Add meat and all vegetables.
Cook for about 1 hour or until vegetables are soft. Season with salt, pepper and butter.
Simmer 30 minutes longer.
I also add some sugar to relieve acid from tomatoes.

title: heart-smart cocoa kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Line 2 large cookie sheets with foil. In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
At high speed, gradually beat in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
At low speed beat in cocoa and almond extract until blended.
Fold in almonds, reserving 1 tablespoon.
Drop mixture by slightly rounded tablespoonful onto cookie sheets.
Sprinkle tops with reserved almonds.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until set. Cool on cookie sheets on wire racks 10 minutes.
With metal spatula carefully loosen and remove kisses from foil.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 2 dozen.
Each kiss:
about 35 calories, 1 g fat, 0 mg cholesterol and 27 mg sodium.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend together broccoli, corn, egg whites, cornmeal, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Crumble tofu to the consistency of cottage cheese and fold into broccoli mixture. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine and combine with bread crumbs and sprinkle over the top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Instead of cottage cheese add 1 can cream-style corn, 1 cup shredded cheese and 2 boxes of Jiffy.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces; set aside. Slightly chop strawberries.
In a mixing bowl, whip together sour cream, Cool Whip and 10x sugar.
In another bowl, mix strawberries and glaze together.
In a medium size bowl, layer cake on the bottom, white filling next and top with glaze.
Continue this until all ingredients are used.
Top with strawberry glaze. Better if chilled 8 hours before serving.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in a little oil.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes. Check with knife inserted in the center.

title: butter flavored brickle drizzles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet with butter Crisco.

title: tamale pie
directions: Pour 2 cans chili into an 8-inch square pan or baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on chili.
Stir 3/4 cup water into cornbread mix.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over chili.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: hot juice drink
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large pot.
Tie spices in a cloth. Add to juices.
Simmer over medium heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Remove spices and serve warm.

title: parmesan breaded portabellas
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a small bowl.
Place mushrooms and flour in a plastic bag and shake to coat.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet on medium heat.
Dip mushrooms in egg mixture and place mushrooms cap side down in skillet.
Saute for 2 minutes per side or until golden brown.
Sprinkle lemon juice evenly over mushrooms.
Remove from skillet and place on baking sheet, bake at 400° for ten minutes or until mushrooms are tender.

title: cherry nut chiffon pie
directions: Makes 2 pies or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour sugar over drained cherries; set aside.
Prepare vanilla wafer, graham cracker or pie crusts.

title: apple streusel ladder loaf
directions: Divide bread dough in half.
On lightly floured surface, roll each half into an 8-inch square.
Spread each square with 1 tablespoon of butter.
In a bowl, combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add apples.
Toss to coat.
Spread half of this mixture down the center of each square.
Cutting from the right edge towards the filling, make 2 1/2-inch long cuts in the dough at 1-inch intervals.
Repeat from the left edge.
Fold strips alternately over filling.
Fold under ends.
Place loaves on a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Brush with milk.
Combine flour and sugar, cut butter into flour and sugar until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle half the crumb mixture over each loaf.
Top with almonds.
Cover and let rise until nearly double (45 to 60 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden. Serve warm.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: "chex" muddy buddies party mix
directions: Measure cereal into large bowl and set aside.
Microwave chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter on High for 1 minute; stir.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal until evenly coated.
Pour into large Ziploc bags.
Add powdered sugar. Seal bag and shake.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine in a saucepan raisins and boiling water, bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes. Cool. Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs; beat well. Blend in raisin mixture and vanilla. Blend or sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice. Stir in chopped nuts. Add to creamed mixture and combine thoroughly. Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheets. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: ratatouille with italian chicken sausage
directions: Cut Italian chicken sausage into 1-inch chunks.
(Sausage is quite soft.
It may be easier to cut partially frozen.)
Saute sausage in 1/4 cup olive oil until lightly browned.
Drain.
Trim and wash eggplant.
Slice.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Trim and wash zucchini, onions and peppers. Slice.
Saute peppers and onions in 1/4 cup olive oil until crisp-tender (about 10 minutes).
Add parsley, garlic, basil, dill and 3/4 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Toss eggplant and zucchini with flour seasoned with 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Dice tomatoes (reserving juices).
Add tomatoes and juice to sauteed peppers and onions.
Add sauteed chicken sausage.
Add eggplant and zucchini. Mix throughly, but do not break up individual items.
Simmer, stirring constantly, for about 30 minutes.
Cook until vegetables are tender, but do not mash.
Blend in Parmesan cheese.
Simmer about 10 minutes longer.
Be careful not to scorch.

title: jiffy beer chili
directions: Lightly brown ground beef and onion in a heavy medium saucepan; cook until onion is soft.
Add tomato paste and beer; stir up brown bits.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add a little water, if needed.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn.
Melt margarine, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, then let boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Turn into large roaster and bake in preheated 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn onto some heatproof surface to cool.

title: easy baklava
directions: Unroll and spread 1 can of crescent roll dough into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press seams together.
Cream together the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread over dough.
Unroll and press seams together on remaining can of dough.
Place over top of mixture.
Beat egg white and brush over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter; gradually add 1 cup sugar and cream. Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with chocolate syrup.
Begin and end with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 28 minutes.
Cool completely. Cream 1/4 cup butter.
Add cups of confectioners sugar and creme de menthe; mix well.
Spread evenly over brownies.
Chill 1 hour.

title: purple basil vinaigrette
directions: In a screw-top jar, combine oil, vinegar, basil, shallot, Parmesan cheese and sugar. Cover and shake well. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve immediately or cover and store in refrigerator up to 3 days. Shake before serving. Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: coconut macaroon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cookie mix with butter packet that comes with the mix, 1 egg white, coconut flavoring and 1/2 cup of coconut in a large bowl.
Stir until blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip balls into remaining egg white.
Roll in remaining coconut.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet (can line with waxed paper to keep bottom from browning too fast).
Press candied cherry half into center of each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes, or until coconut is light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on baking sheet.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: beef rolls cordon bleu
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with salt and vegetable flakes in a large bowl. Shape into 8 patties about 1/4-inch thick. Top each with a slice of cheese and Canadian bacon. Roll up jelly roll fashion.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter; mix soup, cream cheese, sour cream, garlic salt, onion, peppers and chicken.
Line casserole with 1/2 of the tortilla shells, pour in mixture.
Top with remaining tortillas.
Grate cheese on top of tortillas and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: favorite banana muffins
directions: Mix soft margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, baking soda, orange rind, buttermilk and bananas.
Mix until batter is moistened.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 18 regular muffins or 9 Texas size muffins.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and oil.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk; mix well.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in zucchini.

title: polly's chicken with black olives
directions: Brown chicken in a little oil, remove.
Saute onions, garlic, celery and olives.
Add tomato sauce.
Return browned chicken to pan.
Simmer until chicken is tender.
Just before done, add red wine vinegar and steam a few minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: black beans potage
directions: Place washed and picked beans in 4-quart pot, add 2 quarts cold water.
Soak for 2 to 3 hours.
Empty water and refill with clean water.
Bring beans to a boil.
Add half the amount of olive oil, bay leaves and bell pepper.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until almost tender.
In frying pan, add the rest of the olive oil.
Add the onions, garlic and spices to the pan with the oil.
Saute until lightly brown.
Add sherry.
Combine mixture from the frying pan with the beans and continue to simmer until beans are soft.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: brown rice confetti salad
directions: Combine water, rice and salt in pan.
Cook according to package directions.
Remove from heat and cool.
Combine rice, squash strips, broccoli, radishes, scallions, fresh dill, parsley and lemon rind.
Combine 1/3 cup lemon juice, olive oil, mustard and ground pepper in a jar.
Cover and shake vigorously.
Pour over rice mixture.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours. Garnish, if desired.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Mix egg and sugar together in large bowl.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla and mix lightly. Pour into buttered casserole and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time. Add chocolate syrup, flour and nuts.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Nuts may be omitted.)

title: lasagne sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage over low heat in a heavy skillet; drain sausage on paper towels.
Reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Saute onion and garlic in drippings until crisp.
Return sausage to skillet.
Stir in tomato juice, tomato sauce, sugar, salt and bay leaf.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Discard bay leaf.
Combine cottage cheese, egg, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper; set aside.
Cook noodles; drain.
Spread about 1 tablespoon cheese mixture on each noodle.
Roll each noodle, jelly roll style, beginning at narrow end.
Spread 1 cup sausage sauce in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange rolls, seam side down, in sauce.
Spoon with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin apple pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon with apples.
Place in a pie shell; set aside.

title: grilled cornbread
directions: In an 8 or 9-inch foil pan, melt butter.
Turn off heat; swirl butter to coat bottom and sides of pan.
In large bowl beat eggs and milk to blend; stir in creamed corn.
Add muffin mix and stir only until moistened.
Turn into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Place pan on barbecue grill 6 inches above medium hot coals.
Loosely cover top with foil.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: glurb dip
directions: Use a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Spread the cream cheese on the bottom of the pan.
Then pour the Hormel chili over top of the cream cheese.
Last sprinkle the Cheddar cheese on top of the chili sauce.
Put in the oven at 350° and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: eclairs with chocolate frosting
directions: Cook pudding in microwave according to package directions; add 2 tablespoons rum flavoring and cool in refrigerator.
When cold, put in horizontally sliced creme puffs, 1/2 cup per puff.
Spread chocolate frosting on tip and refrigerate until ready to serve. To make frosting, melt chocolate in mixing bowl over hot water. Add sugar and water to chocolate and blend.
Add egg, then margarine and vanilla.
Mix on high speed in bowl of ice water until of spreading consistency.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: In bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, onions, lime juice and peppers.
Blend well.
Spread the filling on the tortillas. Roll up the tortillas and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Cover with wet towel until ready to serve.
Serve with salsa.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Put meat in crock-pot; fill 1/2 way with water.
Cook on high all night.
When done, remove from pot and skim off fat.
Pour all juices from pot.
Break meat apart with fork and return to pot. Add barbecue sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer.
Put on buns and enjoy.

title: lumpiang shanghai
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Wrap 1 tablespoon of the filling in individual Newton pastry wrapper.
Cut into 3 portions and deep fry.

title: potato salad (1)
directions: Wash and cook potatoes.
Add eggs to top of potatoes while cooking.
Dice onions, celery and cooked eggs.
Add dressing.

title: tarragon chicken salad
directions: Chop onion and apples into bite sized pieces.
Cut grapes in half.
Saute chicken in butter and garlic until lightly browned and cooked through.
Use low to medium heat.
Assemble salad.
Cut chicken into cubes; place into large mixing bowl.
Add onion, apples, grapes, mayo and tarragon; mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange salad on bed of lettuce.
Place orange segments around rim.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper, then dust lightly with flour.
In a large skillet, heat butter and oil over moderate heat until foam subsides.
Add chicken pieces, 2 or 3 at a time, and cook over high heat until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Remove to a heated platter and keep warm.

title: grits casserole
directions: Put grits in water and bring to a boil; cook for 5 minutes. Pour in a large bowl.
Add cheese, stirring to melt.
Quickly add eggs, stirring briskly.
Add milk and sausage.
Pour mixture into greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and cook at 400° until casserole bubbles.
Good Sunday brunch or cold winter night supper.

title: goof balls
directions: Melt in double boiler over hot water the caramels and milk. Put a large marshmallow on fork and whirl in the goo.
Then roll in crushed Rice Krispies.
Makes about 50 balls.

title: irish soda bread(1 loaf)
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cut in margarine.
Stir in raisins.
Combine buttermilk and egg; stir into dry ingredients until moistened.
Knead lightly.
Shape into 7-inch ball and put on greased pan.
Cut cross 1/4-inch deep. Brush with milk.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 6 tablespoons juice.
Mix sugar, flour and juice.
Stir in cheese and pineapple; mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Roll cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted butter.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.
Good with ham or grilled chicken.

title: wild rice baked in consomme
directions: Wash the rice well.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add a little water, if rice becomes too dry.

title: sugar-free chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream honey and butter; add egg and mix in flour, vanilla and chips.
Drop on lightly greased baking sheet by teaspoonful.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tar heel pie
directions: Melt margarine and pour over chocolate chips.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: wicky wacky beets
directions: Combine beet and pineapple juice and bring to boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add this and remaining ingredients to boiling juice.
Cook, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. When thick, add beets and pineapple and serve hot.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown the beef in a heavy pot.
Add the onion and garlic. Cook until just soft.
Drain off any excess fat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer for one hour.
Serve warm, garnished with cheese.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and 1/2 stick margarine and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend pumpkin, eggs, milk, brown sugar and cinnamon. Mix until smooth.
Pour on top of first mixture.
Take the 1 cup of reserved cake mix and combine with the white sugar, 1/2 stick margarine and nuts.
Crumble the mixture on top of the pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin; place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion flakes and cut up butter on top of potatoes.
Mix Ro-Tel and soups together.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, spoon into 9-inch pie plate or shallow dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with green onions or tomatoes if desired.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown; drain sausage and set aside to cool.
In a bowl, mix the eggs, salt, milk, dry mustard and sage; mix well and set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the cubed bread, sausage and grated cheese.
Pour the egg mixture over the layers.
Next, pour the melted margarine over the layers.
Cool and cover with foil. Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Set out for 3 to 4 hours before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, loosely covered with foil.

title: scratch pancake mix
directions: Mix together until crumbly the flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and margarine.
Mix together the dry ingredients (1 1/2 cups) with the egg and milk.

title: broccoli with minced ham(serving size: 2)
directions: Wash broccoli in lightly salted water.
Drain and cut off 2-inches from broccoli stems; peel the cut-off stems.
Slice them lengthwise, 1/4-inch thick.
Separate the florets with stems from the large stems.
Cook broccoli and stems in boiling, salted water for 2 minutes, then drain.
Heat oil in wok or skillet; add broccoli and stems.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add salt, sugar and chicken broth.
Mix and bring to boil.
Turn the heat to medium and cook until broccoli is tender, but not mushy.
Mix cornstarch with 3 tablespoons cold water and pour over broccoli.
Add chopped ham and mix gently.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar and flour; bring to a boil until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Cook pie shells and let cool.
Slice bananas in bottom of pie shell.
Add coconut to pineapple mixture and pour over bananas.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Add Cool Whip when ready to eat.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Mix together melted margarine and brown sugar.
Cool; then add eggs, 1 at a time.
Blend in sifted ingredients and add nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Put in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Crack in top is typical.
Cool on rack. Remove from pan in 15 minutes. Store well wrapped.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Pour flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Add egg and mix well. Gradually beat in enough milk to make stiff, smooth batter (no lumps).
Allow to stand for a few minutes, then gradually beat in the rest of the liquid.
This mixture can be allowed to stand some time in cool place before baking.
Before baking, give one final beat.
Pour batter in baking pan, heated with oil or grease from roast.
Bake at 425° for approximately 30 minutes, until brown on top and serve with roast beef gravy.
This is similar to popovers and is delicious.
